(17, ' CDPR\'s worst game (I am serious) ', 'The graphics are amazing, the plot gets more and more interesting, but:\n\n1. The controls are horrible in their current state (double tap to dash in PC ... crouch for skipping dialog ... WHY?!).Here\'s a brief, non-exhaustive list of things the game DOESN\'T give you;\r\n\r\n- Character customization past the initial character-creation (no really, there\'s NONE!)\r\n- A.I. that can match games from 15 years ago\r\n- Wallrunning with the Mantis Blades\r\n- Meaningful choice-and-consequence (seriously; 98% of your choices do NOT matter!)\r\n- The ability to use an NPC as a human shield WHILE firing a weapon\r\n- Vehicle customization\r\n- Weapon customization (a scope and silencer isn\'t enough)\r\n- Player home customization\r\n- The ability to remap keys (double-tap to dodge... really, CDPR?!?)\r\n- Interactions with NPCs (you can\'t converse with 99% of them)\r\n- Interactions with the world (no gambling, no roller-coaster rides, no train rides, no NOTHING)\r\n- Replayability\r\n- Destructability of the game world and its', 2, 'April 14, 2020', 'English', 0, 0, 0, 'BlackMirror', 2093619782),
(18, ' A disappointment', 'Before you complain about not being able to install the game because it\'s not working or you cant find it in gog galaxy, download it from the website by going to Games, click on Cyberpunk 2077 and you\'ll find all the game files. ', 4, 'April 14, 2020', 'English', 0, 0, 0, 'BlackMirror1', 2093619782),
(19, '  Disappointed', 'ut he has nothing to say... . Call can either be denied or cancelled. Ive tried to load three different savegames but Takemura his call always is incoming at same time. Game cannot be saved during call - savegames obvious were corrupted during patch 1.1. Up to latest patch I never had have any problems with bugs on my pc (i7-5820k, X99A-raider, 16GB RAM. GTX980TI, actual driver and bios versions, playing on FHD). Now, I will try to downgrade back to patch 1.06.   ', 3, 'April 14, 2020', 'English', 0, 1, 0, 'bladerunner', 2093619782),
(20, 'Was a QA team even formed for this game?', 'I am completely disappointed in this game. It\'s buggy and you really have no idea where to go or what to do and the first person only option at least in my opinion is less fun. I truly wish that I had never purchased it. ', 2, 'April 14, 2021', 'English', 1, 0, 1, 'BloodRayne', 2093619782),
(21, 'Cyberpunk 2077, an enigma ', 'It will be a great game, in a few years, if the devs add all the stuff they promised and fix the AI...  ', 2, 'April 14, 2021', 'English', 0, 1, 0, 'BloodRayne2', 2093619782),
(22, 'Overmarketed and overhyped ', 'Yet another company I had huge respect for has squandered all the good will they\'ve earned through the years.Thus far I\'ve been spared the worst bugs but make no mistake; there are plenty of bug and glitches...The game also feels lackluster in many areas; no post creation customization, lacks significant dialogue trees and story paths, many parts of the game just feel incomplete.Long story short; the game simply is not finished. It\'s a motorcycle with no seat and one wheel.That being said; It\'s a very nice motorcycle...When the game works it\'s beautiful, engaging, fun, immersive and just feels amazing to play.Needless to say this game has me torn...The game that was released is a broken mess and the decision makers at CDPR should be ashamed for releasing it in this state.That is another thing to remember; this is not the fault of the developers, they have no say in when and in what state the game is released.\r\nThis is another example of suits ruining things for everyone...On the other hand I\'m certain that this game will be absolutely amazing once it\'s finished through patches and updates.Question is if it\'s too little, too late...This was the first game I\'ve pre-ordered in years simply because it\'s CDPR, sadly it will be the last time I pre-order a game and even though I still want to like CDPR the respect I had for them is now gone. ', 2, 'April 14, 2021', 'English', 3, 3, 0, 'BotsHigh', 2093619782),
(23, 'Unplayable', 'The Good\r\n\r\nVisually.. wow.\r\nSoundtrack - fantastic.\r\nStory - interesting and engaging (though i really didn\'t connect with any of the characters)\r\nMain quests &amp; some side quests, unique and typically rewarding\r\n\r\nThe Bad (aka everything else)\r\n\r\nGameplay - often repetitive and bland (maybe 4 or 5 archetypes of missions.. if you\'ve played Far Cry, you\'ve played this game)\r\nProgression - largely pointless (why bother with a 3% increase to blah - when i can just walk into a room, shoot enemies in the face and heal, get a slightly better gun, rinse and repeat - because the enemies are too dumb to bother with any of the progression items)\r\nEnvironment - shallow and lifeless. sure, looks beautiful, but after 5 minutes, you release everything in the world is cosmetic. Almost nothing is interactive, charcaters models and objects repeated over and over (and it seems 2 sex workers service the entire city... no thanks, i\'ll take Judy). The world seems to promise so much verticality.. though almost never leverages it.\r\nAI - oh god. iditotic. NPCs, enemies, police, bosses, friendlies.  just look it up on youtube if you don\'t believe me.\r\nBugs - everywhere. Sometimes hilarious, in my case, sometimes game breaking (had to reload and repeat a good couple of hours work in one instance)\r\n\r\n\r\nDespite my long list of negatives, there are certainly moments where the systems click - and fun can be had. But those moments are few and far between. I really hope they double-down on this game, the way that the No Man\'s Sky team did. It is salvagable. ', 2, 'April 14, 2021', 'English', 0, 0, 0, 'BreakTime', 2093619782),
(24, ' A console port at heart. ', 'Even excusing the hilarious state of the game from a technical standpoint with all the bugs and what not (which I do believe will get fixed), this game is so far from what was promised to us.\r\n\r\nIt\'s not even an RPG. It\'s a linear action adventure game with a few critical choices in a (fairly solid, admittedly) 15-20 hour storyline (albeit with double that content in side story missions which are good), set in an fake open world.\r\nWhy fake?\r\nWell, it\'s an open world for sure, but it\'s hollow. Nothing to do in it. No pedestrian AI, no AI for drivers, no working police AI. Basically, it\'s the most expensive walking simulator with little to no interactivity with the surrounding world. This just screams cut content, so much of it.\r\n\r\nOh, and perhaps most importantly, the gameplay is really mediocre. Sure, you have plenty of fun weapons to use, but enemy AI is worse than in a 2001 game, the character development system is basically just nonsensical percentage boosts for basic stats, and even those basis stats don\'t make much sense. It all feels just cobbled together, poorly.\r\n\r\nOn a positive note, the story and quests are fine, characters are good, the game is beautiful (really stunning) and there\'s excellent music.\r\n\r\nThere\'s a great game buried somewhere in this mediocre mess of cut content and poor design decisions. Not a great RPG for sure, but a great action adventure game, hence my 3/5. With technical stability, I might bump it to a potential 3.5/5, but no more than that. Not with so many broken promises and missing stuff in this shell of a masterpiece that wasn\'t to be.\r\n\r\nCDPR could potentially fixit, if they give it a \'No Man\'s Sky treatment\' everybody seems to be aching for. I personally doubt that will happen, but yes, it could save this one, and CDPR\'s reputation which is gone.\r\n\r\nOtherwise it will remain a testament to corporate greed, poor decision-making and blatant lies to loyal fans.\r\nOh the irony...\r\n\r\nSilverhand would rail against you, CDPR, and so should we.  ', 1, 'April 14, 2021', 'English', 0, 0, 0, 'BridgeConstructor', 2093619782),
(25, ' Feels Like an Unfinished Console Port ', 'I suggest anyone ... wait for another 1/2 year and than \'maybe\' give this game a new try.\r\n\r\nSince December the 10th I feel like beta testing this Game.\r\nI\'m having more frustration with several bugs (small and big ones) than good moments in this game.\r\n\r\nI never had so many frustrating moments again, and again and again with any other game before.\r\nEven Patch 1.1 and 1.1.1 did not seem to change anything on the bugs that I have. ', 3, 'April 14, 2021', 'English', 0, 0, 0, 'Caesar3', 2093619782),
(26, ' Incredible but needs more polish ', 'So, after being in development for so long, this is the final product we get? I can\'t even begin to express how disappointed I am. Not just in the astronomical number of bugs, but also key features and mechanics that are useless or missing from such an overhyped game.\r\n\r\nFirst - the bugs. I have one simple a question; how come CDPR was completely oblivious to the number of bugs in this game throughout its lengthy development? Don\'t get me wrong, I know a large-scale game like this takes time to develop and polish. But literally on my first day of playing this game, I spotted more bugs than CDPR did in the 9 years they spent developing this game. Either the playtesters can\'t do their jobs right, or they deliberately ignored these bugs. Regardless, it\'s a huge loss for CDPR and I can\'t believe they didn\'t see this coming. I\'m not even gonna bother listing out all the bugs I found in this game (not that I can anyway, because of the character limitation). There are plenty of videos on YouTube and forum threads describing all sorts of unpleasant bugs. Not to mention, parts of the world are causing performance issues like framerate drops, etc.\r\n\r\nSecondly - questioning some of the game\'s features and mechanics almost gave me a nosebleed. Like for example:\r\n- Why give us the ability to customise our character if this game doesn\'t even support third person view? I never understood games that do that, it\'s so pointless\r\n- What\'s with this keyboard mapping and why is it so hard to update?\r\n- No vehicle customization? Even something as simple as changing the color? Well that sucks\r\n- Was the wanted system in this game purposefully designed to suck this much? I can kill a cop, then get inside my vehicle and coveniently drive 20 meters around the next block at a slow pace, and my wanted level just disappears. No car chases, no nothing. Makes perfect sense\r\n\r\nHave to cut this short now. Only reason I gave it 2 stars is cause I like the graphics, sounds, weapons and a few of the quests. ', 1, 'April 14, 2021', 'English', 1, 0, 0, 'Carto', 2093619782),
(27, ' A technological mess... ', 'but mediocrity goes down to the core\r\n\r\nI can deal with the glitches as I am not having that bad a problem. The problem is how generic the game is. You can tell how much content there is cut(that or CDPR straight out lied). Instead of a deep RPG we got a Ubisoft open world with a terrible loot system.\r\n\r\nAlso I have suspicion the story changed alot after Keanu Reeves joined in 2018 and the scramble is one of the reasons the game seems very rushed. At first it is like a rags to riches story then once Johnny comes in he is centre stage and everything before that meant nothing. I will even go so far as to say once the Jackie montage was once playable.   ', 2, 'April 14, 2021', 'English', 0, 0, 0, 'CartoonCollege', 2093619782),
(28, ' Great in some areas, bad in others ', 'I will start by whats good with this game.\r\n\r\nTHE GOOD THINGS\r\n\r\nStory - I was very engaged in the story, it was emotional and very well written. You will find many characters that you will grow you like/love and some you will grow to hate/wanting to punch their face in.\r\n\r\nGraphics - The graphics are good. Every new AAA games will have good graphics sooo, thats pretty much it.\r\n\r\nDesign and Visual look of the game - The character design, enviroment, and vehicles are designed really well.\r\n\r\nMusic/Soundtrack - Very good. I am not a Big fan of techno or metal but it works for Cyberpunk and thats what matters at the end of the day.\r\n\r\nNow... to the bad news.\r\n\r\nTHE BAD THINGS/ LIES\r\n\r\nGAMEPLAY - Generic, missed opportunity by CDP.\r\n\r\nBUGS - lots\r\n\r\nAI - Its horrible. The police system is a complete joke. The beautiful city is dead inside.\r\n\r\nMISSING FEATURES - I high recommend people to check reddit about the missing features, its too long for me to write it all down here.\r\nhttps://www.reddit.com/r/cyberpunkgame/comments/kb22xs/compiled_list_of_missing_features_quality_of_life/\r\n\r\nINGAME PHYSICS - Games that have come out almost 10 years ago have better Physics and Ai then this game.\r\n\r\nLIES - They knew what they were doing, yet they still lied to us and told us to expect things are completly missing from the game. High expectation is not this games problem because this game does not even meet the bare minimum. Dont even get me started on console versions.\r\n\r\nI am running out of words so i will wrap this up with this quote by MARCIN IWINSKI Co-founder of CD P.\r\n\r\n\'We hit the ground running with a really good start on PC. While not perfect, its are version of Cyberpunk we are very PROUD of\'\r\n\r\nTo be proud of a version of a game thats barely average, shows how high their STANDARDS are... I will never trust them anymore. Its funny that I see people give this 5 stars, not to bash on other players but to give a game like this 5 stars is to spit on the face of every good game out on the market. ', 3, 'April 14, 2021', 'English', 0, 0, 0, 'cyberpunk2077', 2093619782),
(29, ' The game\'s core won\'t save it ', 'First impressions matter, right? Well, the first impression was great. Seriously. And then something something and boom everything\'s shite.\r\n\r\nThe graphics are top notch, no complaints at all here (if your PC can handle it). The gameplay feels quite good and smooth, different weapons actually behave differently and are fun to use.\r\nSounds are great aswell, the english voice acting is on point.\r\n\r\n\r\nAnd well .. there they were.. my first impressions.\r\n\r\nThe story was goddamn great ... in the very first Act of the game, then everything goes south. Whilst the story is interesting, it isn\'t good, it\'s disappointing at the very best. The game tries to build up tention but \'Hey, have you done those side missions yet? And have you already beat up those thugs and bought that car?\' There is simply too much unnecessary stuff to do.\r\n\r\nBesides the very weak story there are still the bugs everyone was talking about at launch.\r\nWanna climb up that wall to get to the mission quicker? How about the physic engine just kills you instead.\r\nWant to hop in your car real quick? How about the HUD gets stuck and requires you to tinker with the game to fix it.\r\nGot that cool new quick hack thing to lure enemies to you? Yeah, fuck you too, imma teleport back to where I started walking.\r\n\r\n\r\nThe crafting \'mechanics\' and the skill trees are mostly a joke. Nothing much to say here. You can craft a weapon that will be obsolete 2 minutes later because you already killed an enemy and got a better one.\r\n\r\n\r\nTo put it short, I honestly don\'t know what took them about 8 years to release this game. There is nothing major about it. There is nothing that made think like: \'Woaaaahh that\'s sooooo cool, omg!!11!1\'\r\n\r\nThe game as a whole gets about 3,7/10. If you really want to see a good story, character development and an ending that feels good, whether it is the \'good\' or the \'bad\' ending spend your money elsewhere. If you like cluttered games with too many side missions and random stuff, you might very well enjoy this.', 2, 'April 14, 2021', 'English', 0, 0, 0, 'CyberShadow', 2093619782),
(30, ' Useless key binding settings... ', 'I\'m a clown for pre-ordering this ', 2, 'April 14, 2021', 'English', 0, 0, 0, 'DethKarz', 2093619782),
(31, ' Game feels like it\'s in Early Access ', 'So we get a dead, lifeless soulless world, no radio in the car, unusable mouse and keyboard, graphic glitches galore, calling your car in and having it land on another car and then be unusable. Mushy movement, bullet sponge enemies, missing features galore.\r\n\r\nIf this game had taken one year and cost 35 million maybe I could understand this but it took 7 years and 130 million USD as I understand... I do not know what can be said except the management there is at fault to their eyeballs.  ', 2, 'April 14, 2021', 'English', 0, 0, 0, 'Disciples2Gold', 2093619782),
(33, ' Disappointed but not surprised ', 'You cant rebind a lot of controls, its missing promised features, the character customization is lacking, the phisics are buggy npcs constantly get stuck over terrain, the performance is bad, the driving is stiff, you cannot walk on pc theres legit no buttons for it. Braindance is boring after youre first playthrough, the choices you make during the story are mostly pointless, the only choices that matter are made at the end of the game. Theres no barber, or plastic surgeon in a city where \'style is everything\' so youre stuck with the character you make at the beggining.\r\n\r\nAi is terrible, the police wanted system is early alpha at best, the day and night cycle is basically non existent, theres nothing to do in the world aside from shooting people, i completed all the side objectives, the areas of interest and the story under 80hrs, the amount of value you get is lacking when compared to something like Skyirm, Witcher 3, etc.\r\nFor me the biggest disappointment is the character customization, i wanted to go fully borg, and just have all that i can replaced with metal and mech parts, but aside from the hands there are no interesting changes you can make to your character.\r\n\r\nBuy it when you can pick it up for ~20 if it stays in this state.', 3, 'April 14, 2021', 'English', 0, 0, 0, 'DUSK', 2093619782),
(34, ' With a heavy heart... ', 'First 6 hours of game is polished, because this is the part that media was playing.\r\nRest of game is mess, glithes, bugs, cops spawning behind hero (remember their promises about living city, bribing cops etc.?)\r\n\r\nRemember: NO PREORDERS.\r\n\r\nLEAVE GRRED TO OTHERS ', 4, 'April 14, 2021', 'English', 0, 0, 0, 'ExiledKingdoms', 2093619782),
(35, '  Lefties beware! ', 'This game taught me a lesson that not to pre-ordered any games ever again. ', 2, 'April 14, 2021', 'English', 0, 0, 0, 'Factorio', 2093619782),
(36, '  Very disappointing ', 'Eagerly preordered and preinstalled ready to play whne it hit 00:00 Dec 10th, but I\'ve barely been able to play the game becaus eI keep having to go back and adjust the graphics settings to get to some accetapble level - even with settings on a comfortable medium it still looks like GTA Vice City, and when the game so quickly throws you into Night City (as previous reviews mentioned it takes less than 20 minutes to get there so your character origin story doesn\'t really count for much) the quality drops horrendously in setting the atmnoshepere for a game thats all about the immesriveness and atmosphere of its world.\r\nI\'m running it on 16gb with a GTX 1050 ti (I know there are always better graphics cards but for the average working class guy dropping another 500 on a card to play one game is too steep) and cannot express my disappointment high enough.\r\n\r\ntl;dr the game seems great, I just haven\'t been able to get there yet because the system requirements are too high for the average gamer to afford ', 2, 'April 14, 2021', 'English', 0, 0, 0, 'FatesofOrt', 2093619782),
(37, ' Fails as an RPG ', ' was wondering how CD Project Red would deliver their take on a Cyberpunk Scenario. I followed the hype more from a distance, nevertheless followed it since the inital Trailer.\r\n\r\nAfter release, i was first overwhelmed then disappointed and at last a little hopeful.\r\nDid they deliver what was promised? No they didnt. Did they deliver a good piece of Software? No they didnt.\r\nInstead of a expected \'Roleplaying Game\' like Baldurs Gate or at least in the sense of The Witcher we habe a Shooter with Roleplaying Elements. Also the game screems unfinished whenever i play it.\r\n\r\nBut i must confess I like to play it, if you take it for what it is, it is quite entertaining. The Story as i have seen it so far is nothing special and the Missions are well  a \'little\' repetitive, but if you are reading all the text in the mission shards, they give quite some flair to the city even if not played out in the game itself.\r\n\r\nThe Bugs that are in the Game can , if they happen, can be from annoying to gamebreaking, but such things can be fixed. The occurances seem to be diffrent for different computer setup.\r\nThe Missing Features could be added as Free or Buyable DLCs. The Lack of mayor diffences in you choices is lackluster as it prevents to give someone the motivation to replay. But with the upcoming DLCs lets see what will be there.\r\n\r\nOverall for me this is a rushed Game which had the basics implemented. In my opinion it has alot of potential if the Developer adds depth to the Game but as it is i can only give 3 Stars. Maybe i will revise it in the future if CDPR delivers Contant which does the created world justice.\r\n\r\nAll ', 1, 'April 14, 2021', 'English', 0, 0, 0, 'FlatOut', 2093619782),
(38, ' Unplayable at the moment ', '\'m rating this game poorly because it feels unfinished and is a baffling step backward in terms of quality from CDPR\'s last big game. In Witcher 3, even though Geralt wasn\'t my own character, I felt far more invested and had much more control over his development, story, and the fate of his world.\r\n\r\nCyberpunk 2077 starts by building up to you starting from scratch on the mean streets of Night City. However, after a brief intro, suddenly it cuts to a montage, telling you that you did a bunch of cool stuff and now know all the cool people and are pretty cool yourself. I\'ve played a lot of games, but this moment gave me an intense physical reaction I\'ve never experienced while gaming before- a drop in my stomach like, \'uh oh, this won\'t at all be what I\'ve been led to expect this is going to be.\' After the montage, people talk to you like they know you and are your friend but I had no idea how I was supposed to know them or what my relationship with them was supposed to be. It was confusing and disorienting.\r\n\r\nPlaying on Hard, I enjoyed picking skills and feeling overpowered as I cleared icons off the map, but I started feeling bored after 30 hours (I maxed out my level and street cred in about half that). Despite people everywhere, the world feels empty and lonely. Your character and Silverhand are rude and annoying, and I didn\'t care to see how the story would resolve. I felt no need to continue; this is an experience you can have with any dumb AAA open-world game. I uninstalled Cyberpunk 2077 to make space for other games I actually wanted to play, and don\'t have any regrets about it, which is maybe the saddest part about this whole thing for me.\r\n\r\nI\'ll definitely reinstall and play the heck out of this game if it\'s ever finished, but it seems CDPR feels like this is the blockbuster they told us it would be, so this might just be it. I\'m glad some folks have had fun, but unless there are big changes, Cyberpunk 2077 will remain a shallow, irredeemable disaster to me. ', 2, 'April 14, 2021', 'English', 0, 0, 0, 'FlatOut23', 2093619782),
(39, ' Disappointing - Not an RPG ', 'Sorry to say, but patch 1.1 broken my game...\r\n1.06 was working completely fine, now flickering lights, loading textures and volumetrics, tpose every corner, more jagged edges, missing textures(or holes in walls). Now this game look like alpha :( ', 2, 'April 14, 2021', 'English', 0, 0, 0, 'FlatOut28', 2093619782),
(40, ' CDPR, please. ', 'Given the games current state and the pace patches are coming out I\'d say give this game at least 2 more years before you consider buying it.\r\n\r\nIt\'s decent but it\'s nothing more than a shell of what was promised at this point. In a couple years hopefully they will have gotten the game to the state it should have been in at release and it\'ll probably be dirt cheap', 2, 'April 14, 2021', 'English', 0, 0, 0, 'FuckingTest', 2093619782),
(41, ' Not the game I was hoping for ', 'After 30 minutes of play, reloading causes the game to hang and suck up all the free CPU cycles.  On the plus side, this has kept my feet warm.  But there were a lot of cheaper ways to do that.  I want to come back and give a higher rating because I feel a lot of these bugs are fixable with more time.  From the gameplay so far, it\'s worth being concerned that V will not be making any meaningful choices in this game unlike in so many Witcher 3 quests like Ladies of the Wood. ', 4, 'April 14, 2021', 'English', 0, 0, 0, 'GamerAge', 2093619782),
(42, ' See you in half a year ', 'this is a terrible game.\r\n\r\nIt may be because I went in with ultra high expectations and was expecting a Rockstar quality game having played RDR2 and GTAV, but after 60 hours I can quite confidently say this game is trash, forgettable, and should\'ve been worked on for double the amount of time it got.\r\n\r\nBugs aside (something I can deal with), the fundamental mechanics of the game is flawed.\r\nThe looter-shooter genre is a cheap gimmick that should\'ve stayed behind in Borderlands but sadly it\'s infested modern games as a substitute for intuitive and engaging combat. Nothing like dumping more than 10 point blank shotgun rounds into someone\'s head to kill them amirite? (this should never be something that has to happen. ever.)\r\n\r\nThe police system is redundant and useless; teleporting cops that one-hit you, are absolute bullet sponges, and don\'t even chase you in vehicles makes for an undesirable experience. You actually WANT to avoid the police in this game. Not to mention the convenience store flak cannons that one-shot you if you go anywhere in the city with more than 1 star. You guys remember the soldier shown in the 2013 teaser? That model is only used for the 4 star cop, I don\'t even know why you\'d want 4 stars in the first place. So that cool concept is wasted.\r\n\r\nThe city looks great at surface level; great scale, environments, and detail.. only it\'s quite repetitive and, aside from the front door of your apartment, there are ZERO memorable places that make you think \'this spot is lovely, I could just chill here for a while\'.\r\n\r\nAdvertised in the trailer were activities and pass-times to keep yourself occupied in between quests, yet the only activity I\'ve managed to find was the.. embarrasingly boring rollercoaster ride...\r\n\r\nYour choices barely matter, and the ones that do aren\'t significant, some genuinely interesting quests end abruptly with no follow-up, and large portions of the map stay underutilised.. what a waste of potential.\r\n\r\nI could go on but word limit.', 1, 'April 14, 2021', 'English', 0, 0, 0, 'GodHelpMe', 2093619782),
(43, ' Bad first impression ', 'This review was played entirely on 1.06, so I missed any crap before, and any fixes after.  I also intentionally didn\'t watch many trailers, interviews, gameplay videos, etc.  I went into the game expecting an Open World RPG, and that\'s generally what I got.\r\n\r\nFrom a technical standpoint, the game was fine for me.  I had 3 crashes in about 100 hours, and 2 of those were when loading a saved game (saves were fine), and the other was when exiting the game.  There are plenty of bugs, but I didn\'t see anything game breaking.  I missed some side quests because of bugs (I assume...the next step never triggered despite waiting the appropriate time), but they were minor.\r\n\r\nThe world building was excellent, and is both the best and worst part of the game.  It is the best because the game sets you up for some great things.  The big corporations (Arasaka and Militech) are on the verge of war, the Mayor of Night City just died and there is a new election coming, advertisements everywhere, the different areas of the city are actually different, and you can tell what are of the city you\'re in just by looking around.\r\n\r\nIt\'s the worst because none of that really matters.  You can attack Arasaka or Militech all game, and nothing changes.  Despite having some quests regarding the Mayoral election, you change nothing.  Any urgency from the main quest is pure illusion.  You can do side quests forever despite being in a serious time crunch to complete the main quest.\r\n\r\nThe characters are memorable, but I wasn\'t emotionally invested in them.  The plot is well written, but is limited to just the main character.  I don\'t need to save the world, but if I\'m going to attack gangs\' clubs and work with mayoral candidates, I want to see the long lasting impact of those decisions.\r\n\r\nI played the game to completion, and did most of the side quests/gigs/hustles, which means I enjoyed the game overall.  But it didn\'t do anything better than previous games in this genre. ', 3, 'April 14, 2021', 'English', 0, 0, 0, 'GoingCardboard', 2093619782),
(44, ' Not good. ', ' feel like I bought one of those Steam knockoff games with similar titles that are shoved out early to try and piggyback on hype games. Why is it so ugly, why does it run so poorly, why does nothing work like it should? Come on guys, this is just sad. ', 2, 'April 14, 2021', 'English', 0, 0, 0, 'GoodGame', 2093619782),
(45, ' Needed another year / two in development ', 'Man... I have just read the game synopsis on gog store page again, after finishing the game 100%.\r\n\r\nNone of the things written above can be found in the game. The bugs in the game (at lest PC version) are of the least concern. This game unfortunately does not provide the AAA content. Short and shallow (yes!) story and bare bone outdated mechanics...\r\n\r\nI can\'t see how this can be fixed. Game needs total remake. ', 2, 'April 14, 2021', 'English', 0, 0, 0, 'HardWork', 2093619782),
(46, ' Wide as an ocean, deep as a puddle. ', 'Within the first 10 minutes of attempting to play the game, I\'ve haven\'t played more than 2 minutes before the game crashes. A quick search online recommended that I turn off a feature of GOG\'s launcher but, afterward I still have the same issue. I\'m running a RTX 2070 super with 32 GB of RAM, so I\'m pretty sure this isn\'t a hardware issue. I imagine with time this will be fixed but, knowing that does nothing to alleviate frustration now.', 3, 'April 14, 2021', 'English', 0, 1, 0, 'Haven', 2093619782),
(47, ' Decietful Marketing ', 'A terrible buggy mess of a game and with 1.1 CDPR heavily censored this supposedly adult rated game.\r\nStay away. ', 2, 'April 14, 2021', 'English', 0, 0, 0, 'Ink', 2093619782),
(48, ' Shot for the moon, landed in Florida ', 'I hate to say it, but it\'s unplayable for me. It crashes at the exact same point every time in each tutorial. I\'ve tried adjusting settings, even setting everything as low as possible, and there\'s no effect. Until it\'s patched and can be played, I can only give it one star.  I despirately hope there\'s a fix, and we see it soon. ', 2, 'April 14, 2021', 'English', 0, 0, 0, 'IronHarvest', 2093619782),
(49, ' Not A Roleplaying Experience ', 'n short, as a huge fan of the Witcher series and supporter of CDPR, this game was a big disappointment.\r\n\r\nIf you are looking for an immersive role-playing experience with varying choices and consequences, deep lore and character building, you will not get much of that from this game.\r\n\r\nIf you are okay with a run-of-the-mill action game with a short linear main story, a myriad of decent side stories, rather repetitive open-world content, and have the money to burn, I would still advise you to wait until they release all the planned expansions, because by then most of the bugs and glitches should have been fixed, and they may have implemented quality of life fixes or added more content.\r\n\r\nIn its current state, I would not recommend it to anyone, the game feels half-finished in a lot of ways, and there are better, cheaper, games out there which may better suit you, whether you are a role-playing or action game enthusiast.', 3, 'April 14, 2021', 'English', 0, 0, 0, 'JourneytoPlanetX', 2093619782),
(50, ' The same devs as The Witcher 3? ', 'I feel like the game was massively overhyped and underdelivered. There is so much GOOD in the setting that could be expanded on that it it a massive shame that so many things had to be cut from the game and half assed to make the release deadline.\r\n\r\nThe devs are not the blame here though, given enough time they could have polished this into a GOTY product like the Witcher 3 was, but no amount of bugfixers can remedy the cut features and half baked ideas in the game and I will never waste any money on the DLC content they are undoubtedly planning to ram down our throats. ', 2, 'April 14, 2021', 'English', 0, 0, 0, 'KindNessPlease', 2093619782),
(51, ' This one struck a bit too close to heart ', 'The depth of features in gameplay and open world are just subpar for a game that made such ambitious claims about itself. I tried my best to immerse myself in the world and take my time experiencing all the details. At first I was enjoying the cinematic spectacle, but the more I looked the more I realized that the game wasn\'t respecting my level of investment.\r\n\r\nIt kept letting me down in every aspect of game design, with the abysmal NPC and traffic AI and lack of interactivity in the open world being the biggest offenders. CDPR built this enormous vibrant city full of personality and then barely gave us anything interesting to do in it. The aesthetics of the game are absolutely brilliant, but they can only carry you so far before it all feels hollow.\r\n\r\nOnce the honeymoon phase was over for me, bitter disappointment with the all the false promises and wasted potential was the only thing that remained. At best, it\'s an unfinished popcorn flick of a looter-shooter. At worst, it\'s just a bloody waste of time. ', 1, 'April 14, 2021', 'English', 0, 0, 0, 'LastHope', 2093619782),
(52, ' Cyperpunk 2077, FPS not RPG ', '\'ve spent 80 hours in this game and these are my thoughts.\r\n\r\nI, like a lot of people, wanted this game to be great. I finished The Witcher 3 and was amazed by it, and shortly preordering Cyberpunk was available, so I did it. The premiere date was closer and closer, and then CDP Red delayed it. \'Need more time to polish the game\' they said. Well... Fine, I\'m good with it if they deliver better product, i thought. Then they delayed it again. With same excuse. I\'ve waited this long, few extra months won\'t make a difference for me, I thought. And then it finally arrived...\r\n\r\nThis game shouldn\'t be released in this state. It\'s a disaster on many fronts. And while I enjoyed the main story, I quickly discovered that it\'s really railed, and what you do, what background you choose, does not matter. This is my biggest dissapointment. And I feel lied to because this is one advertising of this game was about. It even says it in world compedium included with the game.\r\n\r\nThe world and setting of the game is really good, but this is something CDP Red inherited from buying rights to the Cyberpunk franchise, other then that...\r\n\r\nCDP Red messed up everything they could. The AI is broken, cars are broken, police appears from nowhere, NPCs dissapear, the performance is really bad on lower specd pc\'s, even these within recommended system requirements. Tones and tones of bugs, graphical, physical. Mechanics like crafting are broken. I\'ve spend 50h looting and taking apart weapons, just to discover, that now I have to upgrade components one by one. 8000 uncommon components. And crafting one is taking almost a second. This is ridiculous. Straight up bad game design.\r\n\r\nAnd situation with consoles. Like really, how can CDP Red say that it\'s playable on PS4 when the game runs with 15-20 fps and models are not loading. \'It\'s playable, because the game runs\'. F you. Just say you f\'d up and will do your best to fix it.\r\n\r\nYou can only make a first impression once, and CDP Red forgot that. Shame. ', 3, 'April 14, 2021', 'English', 0, 0, 0, 'Mars', 2093619782),
(53, ' Grand Watchdogs Cry 6. But worse. ', 'I want to like Cyberpunk 2077. I REALLY want to like it. The graphics are gorgeous, but past that, there\'s nothing here to see folks. A middling shooter, with a solid story. A decade of marketing sold this game as THE rpg of 2020, and in an 11th hour shift, its suddenly billed as an action/adventure title. It makes you wonder where all that developement time went. Cars without even basic AI, the inability to even change your HAIRCUT in a world that revolves around body modification, the crouch key and skip dialog key sharing a binding?\r\nIf the only problem this game had was the bugs (of which there is a plethora), I could give this a pass, but the core of this game is hollow. Its pretty. Thats it. ', 4, 'April 14, 2021', 'English', 0, 0, 0, 'MaskOff', 2093619782),
(54, ' Broken keyboard bindings ', 'This is at best an early access right now &amp; if you don\'t have high end hardware then forget enjoying this game right now. Even the recommended hardware specs can\'t acheive stable 60 fps with everything at low. Wait until game gets optimized for older hardwares &amp; then buy.\r\n\r\nNPCs are lifeless &amp; buggy as hell. There are quest breaking bugs &amp; immersion breaking bugs.\r\nGame mechanics like weapon system feels like looter-shooter, no barbers incase you want to change your hairstyles, driving controls are a mess and don\'t give enough feedback.', 2, 'April 14, 2021', 'English', 0, 0, 0, 'MedievalDynasty', 2093619782),
(55, ' My expectations were low... ', 'So I thought waiting for patches would fix this game. Waited until 23rd March 2021 to play it for the first time and in the first three hours I\'ve already seen what people were complaining about. I was so hyped about this game and now grudgingly have to play it to the end because I paid for it', 2, 'April 14, 2021', 'English', 0, 0, 0, 'MegaRace3', 2093619782),
(56, ' The AI is more A than I ', 'I had enough faith in CD Projekt Red to pre-order a game, but it turns out that was a terrible decision. I\'m disappointed by all their awful recent managerial decisions and my heart goes out all the developers who had to work overtime for so long to make this game. And that makes it even harder to say that the final product simply isn\'t good.\r\n\r\nAt its best (or rather: at times) the game is a pretty looking first person shooter with a fun story.\r\nBut as an RPG it\'s bad. Character customization is incredibly limited, with no options to change your appearance in any way after creation. Skill trees are expansive, but most skills on it are very uninteresting. All the story-telling happens in overly long cut scenes and conversations that the player has barely any influence on.\r\nOn top of that there\'s the numerous, sometimes gamebreaking bugs; the NPC\'s terrible AI and an open world that is mostly void of things to do and feels surprisingly lifeless for a cyberpunk dystopia among other things.\r\n\r\nAll of the above is disregarding all the features mentioned during development that haven\'t been realised. I understand that not all content can make it into the final game, but it\'s embarrassing to see how barebones it all is when so much had been promised.\r\n\r\nCyberpunk shouldn\'t have been released like this. As it is, this game just makes me wish I had picked up E.Y.E. Divine Cybermancy instead. ', 4, 'April 14, 2021', 'English', 0, 0, 0, 'MetroExodus', 2093619782),
(57, ' Disappointment of the Decade ', 'First the good news. Game looks great. It sounds great. The acting is great. I guess the story is ok too, if not a bit silly. For a moment it can be immersive too until a game breaking bug snaps you out of it.\r\n\r\nThen the bad and I\'m not talking about bugs here. To my big surprise and disappointment the game has almost zero rpg elements. There is next to nothing taken from the actual Cyberpunk 2020 rpg. You can\'t be whomever you want and you can\'t do whatever you want. Style is nothing. You are mercenary V and no-one else, period. You can choose from three different backgrounds which have absolutely zero effect on your character and story. It only affects the short introductory mission and some dialogue choices. The skills don\'t matter anything. Everybody sees you as the same person no matter what you do and because hacks and stealth are broken as hell, you end up shooting everything anyway.\r\n\r\nStory itself is almost totally linear and flat. You really can\'t influence it. Outside the story there really ain\'t much to do. The world doesn\'t react to anything you do. There is a seemingly big city where you cannot do anything. NPCs don\'t seem to react to anything and when they do they react in a generic way. Reputation system is the most basic one can think of.\r\n\r\nI think you all already know about the completely broken physics and AI, like cops, ducking npcs, etc. so I won\'t go there. They can all be fixed, but until that happens the game is unplayable, unless you just want to experience the main story.\r\n\r\nOverall, if they fix the bugs it can be a nice little shooter. But an RPG? Not even close.', 2, 'April 14, 2021', 'English', 0, 0, 0, 'Minoria', 2093619782),
(58, ' Overpromised, underdelivered ', 'I thought CDPR only release a game when it\'s done. Well, this game is not done at all. I paid a full price for a broken unplayable mess. Sorry but you guys lost my trust....\r\nThe only positive thing I can mention is the graphics of the game. That is nice. But instead of focusing on things like a female character having a penis or having a man voice, you guys should focus on the game itself and to deliver a promised product. ', 2, 'April 14, 2021', 'English', 0, 0, 0, 'MotoRacer', 2093619782),
(59, ' Be warned ', 'At its current state the game feels like an early access project, tons of game breaking bugs, glitches and terrible pc controls optimizacion, the story feels rushed and it\'s definitely not immersive at all. There is an incredibly ammount of missing content.\r\n\r\nI bought the game cause I\'m madly in love with the Witcher 3, the way the story develops and the ammount of freedom when it comes to complete every single quest is amazing, also the world feels endless and every quest is unique.\r\n\r\nThinking that the same team is behind Cyberpunk I expected something better or at least similar in terms of writing, freedom and character development. Instead we got a Grand Theft Auto/Fallout 4 hybrid with tons of repettitve an incredibly boring never-ending side missions. Quantity does no equal quality.\r\n\r\nEverything\'s feels rushed, forced and irrelevant, every decision is meaningless (Fallout 4 all over again). But don\'t get me wrong the game looks amazing and the city is majestic, but somehow it feels empty, it\'s incredible how Night City is filled with npcs but somehow is completely dead, there\'s no soul in this game, it needs at least a couple of years and great dlc content to give this game the soul that so desperately needs.\r\n\r\nKnowing CD Projekt they will fix and improve the game immensely, just like they did with the Witcher 3, to the point to be considered a masterpiece, but it will take a really good amount of time. ', 2, 'April 14, 2021', 'English', 0, 0, 0, 'MotoRacer2', 2093619782),
(60, ' Poor game with a mediocre future. ', 'So after about 100h, this game is overall above average. The world looks great (if you have a $2000 PC, a ryzen 1600 and gtx 1070 has to run at low 1080p to get 60fps) and the main characters are interesting. But I have a few gripes...\r\n\r\n- empty world, most quests are boring and feel like a chore\r\n- AI non existant, youtube a few videos on this. The police might as well not even bother chasing because you can always get rid of them in under 10s\r\n- very demanding to run, like I said. Unless you have a top tier gpu or use DLSS, even 1080p 60fps high detail is hard to maintain. Im sure it looks great if you can run it though\r\n- NOT AN RPG. The game plays more like and Action - Adventure, but some won\'t mind\r\n- Starting class is pointless. Played corpo to start and then the bandit (or whatever its called) for the second playthrough. No difference after 30 minutes\r\n- Limited customization. Cant change car parts/colors, guns, clothes or armor colors, no \'home\' or base changes\r\n- bugs and glitches, to a point. I have only had the game crash 2-3 times, but there have been plenty bugs with AI NPCs, driving and cars, quests, ect.\r\n\r\nIm sure it will be a great game in a year or two, but right now its just \'alright\'. IMO unless you have a high end PC or really want to play now, just wait until 2022 to buy CP2077 ', 4, 'April 14, 2021', 'English', 0, 0, 0, 'MotoRacer3', 2093619782),
(61, ' Mediocre, disappointing, and stale ', 'I guess i\'m in the small minority that has been lucky enough to be able to play the game in a high quality, it looks great and runs okay, i\'ve had small audio issues that were easily solved with a load of an autosave.\r\n\r\nBut with the game being very playable on my end it has made some of the omissions in this game pretty glaring.\r\n\r\n-The driving is pretty bad. not the worst but it takes a solid 15 hours to get used to.\r\n\r\n-The NPCs absolutely DO NOT have a daily routine, the ones you interact with like fixers, and vendors are always there. same with all TWO of the joy toys in the game (this one\'s not a huge deal but to think there are two joytoys in a city like night city is weird) and the non-interactive NPCs walking around seem to just walk in lines and I consistently see the same person walking right b ehind themselves.\r\n\r\n-You cannot play braindances outside of missions at all. you can buy them from the vendors, you have a BD headset but nothing will play on it. in fact there are some missions where you just steal a BD and send it to someone else to watch and tell you about it.\r\n\r\n-There are no activities do to in Night City at all. the races, shooting, and boxing contests are all side missions with story lines to them. you can not play pool, basketball, arcade games, you can\'t even sit down in chairs to just watch peopel go by. I havent even seen an option to watch BDs in the strip club where they are most often talked about.\r\n\r\nhonestly it feels like it was so rushed that they totally skipped over the QA portion of development and even removed a lot of the talked about features just to have something ready for day one.', 2, 'April 14, 2021', 'English', 0, 0, 0, 'NEOScavenger', 2093619782),
(62, ' Mediocre shooter that failed to delvier. ', 'This game makes me sad.  The world is beautiful and the story is intriguing, but its mechanics are so abysmal that it robs me of any desire to play it.  Combat is simply abysmal; every enemy is a bullet sponge so your stealth and tactics don\'t matter, but you can just keep chugging your near-infinite inventory of health consumables until you win.  Every combat is a chore and you absolutely never feel like you\'re a tough and cool street samurai.\r\n\r\nEverything about the UI is terrible.  It\'s filled with inconsistencies; sometimes your clothing can be managed from the base inventory screen, but sometimes you have to go to your backpack to equip an item.  The map would be cool except different icons appear and disappear at different zoom levels, seemingly at random, sometimes in different locations.  The whole thing is just a mess.\r\n\r\nThe one bright spot is the story; it\'s a pretty typical Cyberpunk tale, but it\'s told through well-acted cut scenes.  But even there, the game\'s mechanics are simply bad.  Some dialogue options are timed, some are not, and there\'s no clear reason why.  It doesn\'t seem to matter anyway because the story is completely on rails; the responses you choose allow you to ask more questions but don\'t allow you to change the course of events.\r\n\r\nCDPR may be able to fix some of these flaws and make the game actually fun, but in its current state it isn\'t worth buying.', 2, 'April 14, 2021', 'English', 0, 0, 0, 'NewPage', 2093619782);
INSERT INTO `gogcom_comments_baldursgate3` (`commentId`, `comment_title`, `comment_text`, `game_rating`, `comment_date`, `comment_language`, `helpful_comment_for_all`, `Un_helpful_comment_for_all`, `helpful_comment_for_this_user`, `comment_username`, `comment_gameid`) VALUES
(63, ' PC performance is a major issue ', 'Cyberpunk, by itself, is a average open world game with decent gun play. Memorable characters, and with a plot thats nothing to write home about.\r\n\r\nBUT. if you take into account all the promise they made about the game (Corrupt cops, mercenary\'s, trains, life paths having more meaning then just \'where you want to start\',  in-depth character creation, being able to go into any building you want, etc.) and ultimately LIED about. The current state of the game, being broken and unpolished (even worse on consoles). The fact the this game is NOT a RPG by anymeans, other than perks; which are just basic stat upgrades and lite additions, nothing major. and the world lacks any depth at all that doesn\'t involve gunfights. And the AI is laughable at best.\r\n\r\nThen the game is TERRIBLE in that department. Shame on you CDPR for advertising something that was never going to be, at least from its release date. And using your goodwill from the witcher 3 to essentially boost pre-order numbers and sales for the holidays.\r\n\r\nI\'m glad CDPR\'s reputation has burned to the ground at this point. Hope they think twice before over-hyping a something that isn\'t. And ill think twice before I buy anything from CDPR ever again ', 1, 'April 14, 2021', 'English', 0, 0, 0, 'Noita', 2093619782),
(64, ' Not a true RPG ', 'The game does a few things well, but is plagged by systemic issues which are unlikely to be solved:\r\n\r\n+ Main quests is interesting.\r\n+ Character interactions\r\n+ Night City looks great.\r\n- Lifepath has barely any impact in the game: feels like related quests and content where cut out of the game.\r\n- Barely functional AI makes night city feel soulless.\r\n- Most of the secondary quests are filler.\r\n- Random open world events are basic and uninteresting.\r\n- RPG mechanics barely impact gameplay and feel lackluster.\r\n- Itemization is horrendous: you are showered by huge ammounts of barely better loot.', 3, 'April 14, 2021', 'English', 0, 0, 0, 'OlliOlli', 2093619782),
(65, ' Crash Bandicoot Without the Bandicoot ', 'Cyberpunk 2077 feels like a tech demo for RTX that had a game tacked on.\r\n\r\nI have had endless bugs including two game breaking bugs that caused a restart at around for and eight hours in, respectively. I pushed ahead and was lucky that I did not get another game breaker on a story mission. I have close to four hours of horrendous bugs and quest/questlines that just fail to progress. I had two sets of hands one of which was fully extended mantis blades and the other my actual hands. This bug persisted for nearly three hours even after restarting the game, restarting the system, and installing all three of the other arm weapon options. The arms returned to normal for no discernable reason when I crashed into a car while riding a motorcycle. Thankfully, I only had three crashes. During key points of the final few missions I had to reload the game several times as the characters would get stuck in conversation or on objects, ruining my immersion completely. The performance is all over the place. Pop in is exceptionally bad in certain areas regardless of graphics settings.\r\n\r\nThe RPG mechanics are awfully basic especially regarding skill trees with the primary benefits being ad 5% damage or charge a weapon faster. There are some that stand out but for the most part it is awfully simple, and many skills make skills in other trees redundant. Your choices matter does a degree however you more or less get a different skin of the same ending no matter what choices you make (with one being better than the others).\r\n\r\nThe writing in the game is incredibly inconsistent, some quests and story lines truly immersed me in the world that is Night City and the lives of the characters I was interacting with however there were moments in the game where I physically cringed at the dialogue.\r\n\r\n\r\nThis game is not worth your money', 1, 'April 14, 2021', 'English', 0, 0, 0, 'OnceUponAtari', 2093619782),
(66, ' Wait for the \"Complete Edition\" ', 'the minimum and recommended system requirements are a bad joke. Strictly speaking, this is an early access game sold at full retail price. Pretty unethical behaviour by CDPR which I didn\'t really expect at all.\r\n\r\nThis is not acceptable and I\'ve requested a refund. ', 1, 'April 14, 2021', 'English', 0, 0, 0, 'Outlast', 2093619782),
(67, ' A mediocre experience ', '+ solid gameplay loop\r\n+ nice characters\r\n+ stunning graphics\r\n+ tons of nice secondary quests\r\n+ nice soundtrack\r\n\r\n- bugged like crazy\r\n- RPG part non-existent, none of the choices you make during the games have consequences\r\n- mediocre main plot with open endings that don\'t make sense\r\n- loot system completely broken, should be remade from the ground up\r\n- tons of cut content and they don\'t even try to hide it\r\n- Night City looks gorgeous but feels really empty\r\n- 2 of the 6 skill trees are totally useless\r\n- mediocre (at best) shooting\r\n- controls on M/K are trash\r\n- FPV only\r\n\r\n\r\nCP2077 is not a RPG. It\'s an action game with an inventory and I find it pathetic and disrespectful.\r\nCDPR lied and the only thing we can do is hope they fix this damn game.\r\nDon\'t buy it. Wait for the GOTY, Definitive Edition or whatever, it needs at least another year of polish and content to be worth 60.', 2, 'April 14, 2021', 'English', 0, 0, 0, 'Overcooked!2', 2093619782),
(68, ' Huge letdown. ', 'This is a game that sets you up for disappointment. Not because it\'s bad and you\'re disappointed that you wasted your money on it, but because it\'s so good you can\'t help but feel disappointed at the fact that you could have had a better game if it wasn\'t so short.\r\n\r\nThe different lifepaths idea feels unfulfilled. It doesn\'t have much of an impact apart from the start of the game. Sure, you\'ll have a few different lines with characters depending on which lifepath you started with, but that\'s it. It doesn\'t give you content exclusive to the lifepaths you choose.\r\n\r\nThe \'Braindance\' thing is annoying because it sounds fascinating, but it ends up as an underdeveloped concept.It only appears a few times during certain missions. The way it was used feels as if it existed solely for plot convenience. You carry around a headset everywhere, but you don\'t ever use it apart from the few instances where you are asked to use it for a mission.\r\n\r\nCustomisation in the game is practically non-existent. When creating your character at the start, I was surprised at how limited it was, given the way it was marketed. I was not allowed to customise V\'s home, nor get new ones by myself (apart from getting new apartments via Judy/Panam/River, where their apartments became mine as well) You cannot customise the cars that you bought either.\r\n\r\nThe game\'s main story, and world is the most disappointing part. The world, while pretty to look at, feels very empty. The enemy AI is really dumb. The main story feels very abrupt at times, (you get introduced to Jackie, undergo a time skip, suddenly the 2 of you are best buds, then he dies.) The game tells you that you have a choice, but you don\'t, not really. You just get to choose how you get from point A to point B. I loved the side quests, but there is very little side quests for you to do. I hate that I get attached to characters easily because the game either kills them off, or isn\'t long enough for you to really get to know them. ', 2, 'April 14, 2021', 'English', 0, 0, 0, 'PatientEnd', 2093619782),
(69, ' A better FarCry game, not more ', 'f I didn\'t know that CP2077 were made by the same people who made \'The Witcher\', I would never believe it was from the same company.\r\n\r\nI had quite a lot of fun with the game, truth to be told. However, the last part felt so rushed and all the choices I\'ve made throughout the story was... Well, totally meaningless.\r\nWhen I\'ve finished the final mission, I thought the next chapter would start. Well, no, game over and a slap in the face with a terrible final cutscene.\r\n\r\n8 years of waiting for this. Never been so disappointed.', 1, 'April 14, 2021', 'English', 0, 0, 0, 'PODGold', 2093619782),
(70, ' I did not expect this from CDPR ', '- no RPG (not even close to the witcher 3)\r\n- main-story on the quality level of Watchdogs\r\n- loot system = trash you dont need everywhere\r\n- bugs still not fixed, will take years I guess\r\n- AI and logic on a beta-game level\r\n- city and NPCs just decoration and useless\r\n- after finishing the main-story, have fun with 200 boring missions left ', 2, 'April 14, 2021', 'English', 0, 0, 0, 'PositronX', 2093619782),
(71, ' Beautiful to look at but not fun at all ', ' don\'t care much about the bugs because they can be fixed later on after the game has been released. And afaik, none of the bugs are actually game breaking. So, I can accept that the game was rushed and there are a lot of bugs.\r\n\r\nWhat I can\'t accept is the fact that the story is lackluster at best. Just when I thought the story was getting interesting... it ended abruptly. Wtf? Here I was expecting a game similar to The Witcher 3 in terms of the content (story, characters, dialogue, quests, monster equivalent etc.) and what I got was not even 25% of that. And to top it all off, some of the side quests end abruptly (like the Peralez quest line).\r\n\r\nLet\'s compare. Witcher 3 has in total 200+ quests out of which 57 are main story quests. This game has around 50 quests IN TOTAL.\r\n\r\nThe reason players loved Witcher 3 so much is not because of the graphics, not because of the gameplay, not because of the sandbox environment created by the game, not because of the mechanics etc. The one and only reason people still play The Witcher 3 today is to experience the story and side quests. The Witcher 3\'s story and side quests are long, very long. But that\'s what separated CDPR from the rest. The Witcher 3 is so massive that if you have played it once, you can literally forget 95% of the quests and play it fresh from memory a few years later on.\r\n\r\nThey created this huge dense map which is honestly one of the best city maps if not the best city map in any game ever. But they themselves didn\'t utilize this map to its fullest. Around 50% of the map is not explored by any quest ever. So what\'s the appeal of playing it other than playing the quest then? One can only explore and be awed by a map so much.\r\n\r\nIf I had to break it down where their funds went, it would be: 50% for the map, 20% for the mechanics, story and overall content and 30% for marketing. I am not even kidding. This might actually be correct. Its such a shame. I will never look at CDPR the same way again.  ', 4, 'April 14, 2021', 'English', 0, 0, 0, 'PrinceofPersia:WarriorWithin', 2093619782),
(72, ' Scam', 'I\'ve put in around 160+ hours into the main game, side quests, roaming the city... and finally gave up.  I enjoyed finding the hidden easter eggs, the large expanses to explore, battling the various gangs however after a while it just got stale.   It just became tiring.  There was so much promised and it becomes so obvious that so many things are unfinished and missing.  Such a great disappointment.  I hope CD Projekt Red can salvage their name and this game however I don\'t really know if that\'s possible.  I put in nearly 600 hours into Witcher 3 and return over and over to that world however I really don\'t think I\'ll ever return to this game. ', 2, 'April 14, 2021', 'English', 0, 0, 0, 'PumpkinJack', 2093619782),
(73, ' Not a very good game... ', 'Sadly Cyberpunk is NOTHING like what was promised. For ages we saw videos and interviews explaining all the amazing features that would be in the game. All the cool mechanics. All the new ideas that would make it stand out and unique.\r\n\r\nIn the end, we got a bare bones open world shooter, that fails on almost every level.\r\n\r\nCharacter development is practically non-existent. There\'s stats and skills (which are mostly just passives) that can slightly improve your character in certain regards. However all the gameplay is still 100% reliant on PLAYER skill, not character skill. So if your FPS skills are good, you\'ll breeze through the game. You can have no stats or skills tied to using gun, grab a pistol and just slaughter your way with ease.\r\n\r\nThe weapon system is poor. There\'s a variety of guns, which mostly all do the same thing, and have wildly randomized stats. So you might have two versions of the same pistol with one doing three times the damage as the other. So getting good gear is entirely luck based. And the horrific crafting system doesn\'t help with that. The gear you craft is just as random, so you might waste a lot of materials trying to make something that\'s not garbage.\r\n\r\nThe AI is non-existent. In combat, enemies mostly either stand in the open shooting (when they don\'t ignore you completely) or duck behind cover and just sit there. No flanking, no tactics, just target dummies. NPC\'s on the street are bland and lifeless, and usually just sqaut in place if a shot goes off (and disappear if you turn your back). The vehicle AI is also just not there. Cars follow set paths on the road, they won\'t swerve or avoid obstacles, they\'ll just stop and sit there forever. They also disappear when you turn away.\r\n\r\nThe \'open world\' is dead and lifeless. No minigames or distractions like every other open world. Just a thousand \'go here, kill/stealth guards, take/hack X\' missions, repeated endlessly.\r\n\r\nBasically none of what was promised was delivered. Don\'t waste your money. ', 2, 'April 14, 2021', 'English', 0, 0, 0, 'Pyre', 2093619782),
(74, ' Genuinely disappointing. ', '\'m running a combination of recommended and high end specs on my machine. Needless to say, I expected to be able to turn settings in this game to low to be able to achieve a stable 60fps if not more. I\'m disappointed to say that in its current state that simply isn\'t possible, especially when the game only utilizes 10-30% of my gpu and 50% of my CPU. The game looks and plays horrible on consoles as well. Given that this game has been in dev for 7 years, and was supposed to come out earlier this year, it leaves me with one major question. Who was this game made for? It certainly wasn\'t mid-low spec PC gamers or last gen gamers. So you\'re looking at around 10% of the market now. On the topic of PC gamers, YOU CAN\'T TURN OFF MOUSE ACCELERATION. THIS IS A SHOOTING GAME. Seriously CDPR? Seriously disappointed to say the least. ', 3, 'April 14, 2021', 'English', 0, 0, 0, 'RacetheSun', 2093619782),
(75, ' Buggy and unoptimised mess ', 'Good:\r\n- visually stunning\r\n- impressive and immersive gameworld\r\n- very cool and interesting setting\r\n- well made and unique characters with their own personalities\r\n- good and interesting story (Act1 being the best part of it imo)\r\n- good in depth character customization\r\n\r\nBad:\r\n- linear story for the most part, choices don\'t matter really in the main story\r\n- your lifepath basically doesn\'t matter\r\n- endings are a huge let down imo (makes everything you did before feel like you wasted time)\r\n- cannot continue after the last main quest (have to load a save before point of no return)\r\n- wasted potential with Romances -&gt; only lame dialogue after completing romance (can\'t even sleep at your partners home)\r\n- people on the streets are as basic as it gets (10 year old games have better passerbys)\r\n- AI needs rework especially Police\r\n- controls on keyboard are kinda strange and cannot be remapped\r\n- cannot change characters look mid game (not even the hairstyle)\r\n- AI spawing and despawing when off screen\r\n- loot -&gt; 95% of the time I get grenades or consumables which I don\'t even need and/or use\r\n- bugs\r\n\r\nOK:\r\n- driving\r\n- combat and stealth (little bit clunky at times)\r\n- general movement\r\n\r\nConclusion:\r\nFor a game advertised as a RPG it lacks many RPG elements especially in the story and the choices you can make or better cannot make. The choices you make are mostly irrelevant and don\'t have any real consequences in the long run. You cannot \'write\' your own story like in many other RPGs (like the Fallout- or TES-series). This really diminishes the replayability imo as the story basically always plays out the same way except for minor changes. As someone who likes to write his own unique story in RPGs this is a huge let down.\r\nI hope that DLCs or patches (maybe mods) will fix some of these story and choice related issues I have.\r\n\r\nI still had a good time playing it so far but I would not recommend it at the current state.\r\n\r\nNot the Masterpiece many claim it to be (not even close). ', 2, 'April 14, 2021', 'English', 0, 0, 0, 'RedFaction', 2093619782),
(76, ' Not RPG ', 'Plays exactly like Crash Bandicoot without the Bandicoot. Don\'t worry though once you get past the crashing a game world devoid life and AI awaits:\r\n\r\nNo driving AI. Cars will stop if blocked and wont try to path around anything.\r\nI don\'t see anybody get inside cars.\r\nPolice don\'t drive cars ever.\r\nPolice spawn behind you and forget everything if you walk 1 block away.\r\nNo bounty system like promised.\r\nAI pedestrians don\'t have patterns like promised they spawn (sometimes in duplicate clones) and despawn that\'s it.\r\n80% of the cool shops/Bars/Food vendors are devoid of any interaction.\r\nNo mini games.\r\nCar physics are awful.\r\nAI will glitch in fights 1 out of 4 times.\r\nNo rep system with any factions that I noticed.\r\n\'Your choices will have effects that ripple through the city\' More like a stagnate swamp with annoying bugs stinging you.\r\nThe intro they were showing us is in the game but that\'s it. After it feels like a completely different game.\r\nOdd things like 20 dildos being programmed but not a single one can be used for anything. Did we really need that many dildos without a use?\r\nFor a game that allows you to customize your genitals it is strangely devoid of sex/nudity (after the intro they show everyone of course).\r\nFake choices, your dialogue options are meaningless.\r\nSometimes the entire block of pedestrians will just hunker down and run for no reason.\r\nNo pedestrians react or talk other than \'hey whats up\' \'...?\'.\r\n\r\nThis game is worse than games made over a decade ago. And while a game doesn\'t have to always be better than another game to be fun, it does when you make comments like \'most immersive city\' and \'branching options that have rippling effects\'. When you pitch your game as being something new while casting shade on competition and you can\'t even compete with their games that were released over a decade ago. Heck this game can\'t even compete with Witcher 2..... ', 2, 'April 14, 2021', 'English', 0, 1, 0, 'RedFaction2', 2093619782),
(77, ' What happened CDPR? ', 'Currently I suggest waiting a year or so for them to actually REALLY finish the game. Unless you find the AI not being able to figure out how to follow you around a corner \'Peak Gameplay\'. Good AI will save a game, bad AI will bury it in a pit of boredom. Currently they can\'t figure out how to shoot you when you\'re both in plain sight, can\'t figure out how to get in to melee range when using melee, can\'t figure out how to stop hiding in cover when you\'re basically clearly flanking them, can\'t seem to figure out that throwing a grenade at a wall infront of their face might be bad for their continued existence. Interesting game, but also needs probably another year of polish at the rate things seem to be going.', 2, 'April 14, 2021', 'English', 0, 1, 0, 'RedFaction3', 2093619782),
(78, ' Great potential, incomplete experience ', 'title says it all, this isn\'t about the bugs nor the performance issues. The game content itself is the problem. In general it feels like a lot of content has been cut out. Overpromise but underdeliver. Hype should not be blamed, devs have repeatedly advertise the game with so many elaborate features and mechanics through interviews, trailers etc but we only see like 20% of it in game.\r\n\r\n-Main story, pretty much just average, feels more like Johnny\'s story rather than the player\'s\r\n-Endings are ok, bittersweet tone but nothing spectacular\r\n-Side quests like gigs, secondary quests, radiant events are a huge disappointment. They are mainly to farm exp, cred, money, gear mats etc. They lack a soul, theres no good storytelling\r\n-The promise of branching storyline, decisions that matter, actions and consequences are unfullfiled.\r\nStories and quests are more or less standalone with poor storytelling. They don\'t interact or effect each other, the main story or even the world. So called decisions are only for the 7 endings which mind you is basically loading a save and choosing the other option.\r\n-Lots of missed opportunities. An example being the different factions of the Cyberpunk world. They can be better used by having them as factions that players must choose to align with that effects the main story, but we get none of that here. Life paths are pointless as they have no importance except some dialogue and a short quest.\r\n-Romance is a hit or miss. I liked Panam\'s, others were meh. Devs tried to be inclusive but it backfired and we get only 1 romance option per gender/sexuality.\r\n-Characters and companions are forgettable and a disappointment, lacks the quality and storytelling you see in games like Witcher 3, Dragon Age Origins or Baldur\'s Gate.\r\n-Too much focus on looter shooter GTA open world style gameplay, sacrificed all other RPG aspects.\r\n\r\nCyberpunk 2077 really feels like they had big dreams but overestimated their abilities, ran out of budget and cut 80% of the game out. ', 2, 'April 14, 2021', 'English', 0, 0, 0, 'RewindThis!', 2093619782),
(79, ' Above average, but let down ', 'A lot of the contents mentioned during the dev streams were removed. AI sucks, pointing a gun at someone who is inside the car does not trigger any response at all. Police suddenly spawns out of nowhere and for some reason does not use any vehicle. Car chase with shootouts are scripted, will have the same result whether you shoot or not. Hitting a traffic then rotating your camera to the point where the vehicle you\'ve rammed can no longer be seen and rotating it back again magically repairs the dents in that vehicle and places it back in the road as if you\'ve never rammed it. NPCs do not steer the steering wheel when steering. Customizations are limited compared to what was promised. Prologues does not matter, it is just a short 10 minute introduction and after that a rushed cinematic to make you care about someone who you are supposed to care for but since it is rushed, it is very hard to develop emotional attachment to said character. Character shadow movement looks like Woody from toy story. NPCs say the same thing over and over again. NPC mouths sometime doesn\'t move when talking to them. No water physics when you shoot or drive through them. Decisions barely make an impact on story except for some select few dialogue options. Children are like downscaled models of adults. No random encounters and many other immersion breaking bugs or features. The game promised immersion but feels like a half baked RPG. Would\'ve understood it if the game was released 8 years ago but for a 2020 AAA game? Several other older games were able to do better except for its graphics. The only thing worth praising in the game is the graphics and the story but it is very hard to immerse yourself in the story when the game world is doing its best for you not to. ', 3, 'April 14, 2021', 'English', 0, 0, 0, 'RimWorld', 2093619782),
(80, ' bugs aside.. ', 'This game is unplayable at this state, NPCs walking through walls, key binding is not existent, the game\'s mechanics aren\'t explained at all.\r\ni will refund it. ', 2, 'April 14, 2021', 'English', 0, 0, 0, 'Risen', 2093619782),
(81, ' Undercooked doughnut without filling ', 'First of all yes there are bugs, control and balance issues.  These can be fixed given time and I\'m not including those in this review.  This is regarding what the game is and isn\'t.\r\n\r\nFor a game based on a RPG, Cyberpunk 2077 is lacking a great deal of the Role Playing aspect.  The main story line is rigged from the end of Act 1 and it put a significant downer on my interest in both the character and the game in general.  I have a second character that is locked in one area of the game due to avoiding the dead-end main story.\r\n\r\nCharacter creation is ok, you are limited in the physical build of your character to male or female and therefore the options are mostly cosmetic with some minor options to change the face.\r\nAll the cyber options your character has are subsurface.  During the game you\'ll see people wearing a number of replaced limbs and body parts in various styles, CDPR used these a lot in the media and none of them are available to you.  I feel this was a lie perpetrated by CDPR.\r\n\r\nThe three life paths (Nomad, Street, Corp) are nothing remotely resembling the narrative that CDPR pushed in the media.  Other than a very short prelude the choice you make has no further use other than the odd option during conversations.  Essentially the significance of the life path choice was a lie.\r\n\r\nThe city could have been Steelport from Saint Row 3 for all the feelings of a futuristic corrupt city it generates.  The various gangs are set encounter points and have no point in the game beyond giving you the same foe in different styles to kill/disable, no gang v gang territorial fighting etc.  Your actions don\'t cause a reputation change with a target gang, the police or the other gangs.  Street Cred is purely to control access to equipment.\r\n\r\nWhat CDPR released is nowhere near the game they pushed in the media it is, it could have been great but as of this review it is poor.  The best it is likely to achieve with all the patching and updates is a mediocre OK', 2, 'April 14, 2021', 'English', 0, 0, 0, 'SaintKotar', 2093619782),
(82, ' Shallow as a Puddle ', 'This is a review that I\'d hate to write. But it had to be done.\r\nCDPR has lost their way, drunk in their own glorious past.\r\n\r\nI didn\'t follow the news on this game\'s development closely.\r\nI never did jump onto that hype train.\r\nI ran the game on a decent pc setup, and throughout my full playthrough, I didn\'t experience any game breaking bug at all, apart from some hilariously immersion-breaking visual glitches.\r\n\r\nSo why did I rate this game as a mediocre game at best, and speak so terribly about it?\r\n\r\n[The UI and gameplay design]\r\nThis game\'s UI needs a lot of work. There\'s no multi crafting / dismantling button.\r\nThere\'s no warning or confirmation button for dismantling Iconic equipments, so if you accidentally dismantle them without looking, the whole upgrade tree is gone forever.\r\n\r\n[The AI]\r\nThe enemy and police AI needs A LOT of rework. Police simply spawn out of thin air behind you, and never give chase on vehicles. You can even just sprint away to remove the bounty.\r\nEnemies will just cower in cover even when you\'re using a cover-piercing sniper rifle, making many combat encounters meaningless.\r\n\r\n[The Factions]\r\nYou can slaughter hundreds of a particular faction\'s members, and it won\'t affect your standing with ANYONE. In fact, they\'re all (including their leaders) are just there as props.\r\nI solo butchered the entire top echelon of one of the factions in the main story, and they\'re supposed to be this all-powerful and enigmatic cabal of netrunners. They were written in just for the sake of writing. Which brings me to the next point..\r\n\r\n[The Writing]\r\nThe writing of this game is polarized. It can be quite good for the main story missions, but horrible for the side gigs.\r\nLizzy\'s gig is an example of this. At the conclusion of the gig, there\'s no option to report her to the MaxTac officers right across the street, or kill her.\r\nYou can only either help her, or not. Such lazy writing.\r\nDon\'t let me even start on how lazy the \'lifepaths\' system is.', 2, 'April 14, 2021', 'English', 0, 0, 0, 'Sanitarium', 2093619782),
(83, ' This is early access ', 'I am a PC owner so this review is only for the PC.\r\nI am putting a list of how I as a fan of Project Red and a 1st day owner of all 3 of their Witcher Games rate this highly awaited Game. It has been a great disapointment to me because it is not a true RPG, it is a FPS with a nod to some RPG points which so far I have found do not in any way perform as they are supposed to. I have taken the Tech skill to level 8 which is supposed to let you open locks, it failed on locks marked six and seven, BROKEN, what other aspects of the skill and perks tables do not work I have yet to find out. Next point the game is linear not open world, regardless of which option you choose Nomad, Street Kid or Corp the result is the same. No matter which choices you select in all cases they will result in the same conclusion.\r\nYou will always end up with a companion called Jackie, he cannot be killed util you have completed the quest for the relic chip. But a rider on this he is absolutely useless in that he does no discernable damage to your enemies, his only use is as a distraction. Regardless of what you do he dies in the car on completion of that quest. LINEAR.\r\nWith my second avatar I tried to delay doing the relic quest but found out I could not return to my flat and could only use the map to find side quests and complete them Solo as you can have no companion.\r\n\r\n1.	game is not RPG it is FPS.\r\n2.	Graphics 4 star.\r\n3.	Voice acting 5 star.\r\n4.	Controls 1 star.\r\n5.	Game play 1 star.\r\n6.	Immersion/Replay 1 star.\r\n7.	Value for money 1 star.\r\n\r\n Graphics gets 4 because of the people materialising and disappearing in front of you and also if you want to try, hold W and shift and aim for the people in a crowded street, you pass through them as though they do not exist except for the odd one.\r\nIn conclusion I have 11 hours play and have taken 2 of the 3 avatar options to the end of the relic quest and a bit further.    ', 2, 'April 14, 2021', 'English', 0, 0, 0, 'Screamer', 2093619782),
(84, ' Disappointing ', 'The teaser was revealed somewhere between FC3 and GTA5 releases (that was the first time I\'ve heard of Archive and I enjoyed every last of their songs since then). And the game stayed true to 2013 while being released 3 weeks before 2021. With added \'benefits\' of being a console port.\r\n\r\nUI is simply awfull, controls were designed for people with major chrome augmentations - 10 fingers with 11 digits each will do just fine, enemy AI and thrilling combat - nonexistent, likable characters - couldn\'t find any so far, crucial moment of the story - an hour of the most predictable and clishe tosh I\'ve seen  in years.\r\n\r\nFor 13 hours I\'ve tried to find anything redeeming this \'Best Role-playing Game of 2020 with no role-play in it\' of the sin of being simply boring. To no avail.\r\n\r\nWas it worth the money I\'ve spent? Well, it costed and lasted as if I\'ve watched 5-6 movies in cinema, so - yeah, I\'m not applying for a refund even if I could. Was it worth the time, wait, hype, expectations? No, definitely not. ', 2, 'April 14, 2021', 'English', 0, 0, 0, 'Screamer4x4', 2093619782),
(85, ' It\'s just not very good... ', 'I do not understand how you can customize your junk, but not which keys you want to use to play the game.  The whole keyboard binding is janky and a mess.  Forced to use the TAB key for activating your cyber gear - then you have to use the F key to interact with stuff.  Can\'t change it with the interface in game - and I\'m too disappointed to do it manually by editing some usersettings.json file.\r\nMy multi-button mouse is basically useless and I do not game with a controller - this is a computer.\r\n\r\nYes the game is pretty - but if I can\'t configure the game so I can move and interact like I want to - then I\'ll just go back to a game where keybindings work, like AC Odyssey. ', 2, 'April 14, 2021', 'English', 0, 0, 0, 'SilentService+2', 2093619782),
(86, ' Bugs with Censorship included ', 'The quality of the product delivered was below my rock bottom expectations. When we heard that CDPR is delaying the game time and time again, I\'d thought that they\'re actually polishing the game, not scrambling to glue the puzzle pieces together. Until a majority of common bugs are fixed and the game is more optimized my score will remain as is.', 2, 'April 14, 2021', 'English', 0, 0, 0, 'SilentService1+2', 2093619782),
(87, ' Badly Bugged. ', 'In some aspects its amazing, but unfortunately these aspects are very shortlived. Quests can be fantastic, but they\'re never at the level of Witcher 2, 3 or Thronebreaker.\r\n\r\nAll optimization and bug issues aside (which to be honest is about 15-20% of the game) the game is not nearly as tightly written as their previous titles.\r\n\r\nI\'ll give you the most blatant example, just coming out of Act 1, you JUST have a life and death moment with a certain character. You then exit the building your in, get in your car and suddenly get smashed into by a psycho AI car, no biggie, sounds interesting. Only for your V to then react calmly, asking the person WHO WAS JUST TRYING TO KILL YOU if they saw that you just saw. Are you seriously telling me no one in CDPR thought this was a glaring inconsistency STRAIGHT OUT OF THE PROLOGUE? Literally the first thing that happens is completely inconsistent with the tone of what immediately preceded it.\r\n\r\nGameplay wise its meh, I enjoy the shooting but I don\'t love it. Its very very bullet spongey which makes me feel like I\'m playing a worse off Borderlands, and its very loot filled which gives off Deus Ex Mankind divided vibes, only 99% of stuff is trash.\r\n\r\nThe bit thats REALLY grinding my gears though is the AI. Fixing something like this isn\'t possible, because there\'s nothing to fix - the AI isn\'t broken, its not there at all. Why in 2077 would police chase you ON FOOT rather than getting into their cars? How do they suddenly spawn behind you after you commit a crime despite you being in the middle of nowhere completely alone? Why do the NPCs not only all look exactly the same but do exactly the same thing, which is absolutely nothing, when interacted with? I watched a guy walk up to a chinese food stand, only to pull out a pizza FROM HIS POCKET.\r\n\r\nThere\'s so much more to talk about in terms of whats wrong with this game but I don\'t have enough characters left to do it. This game simply isn\'t good enough in its current state. ', 2, 'April 14, 2021', 'English', 0, 0, 0, 'SleepFunction', 2093619782),
(88, ' Disappointed', 'Ladies/gents/non-binary/gender fluid/whatever, this game is a total disappointment. CDPR appears to have pulled a classic page out of Peter Molyneux\'s playbook by making big claims about what this game will have and what you will be able to do with your V. Bold claims that turned out being totally false. There is all kinds of jank in this game. Bethesda would be proud!\r\n\r\nThe footage we all saw almost 2 years ago was bullshot. The pre-rendered graphics we all saw looked stunning. Unfortunately the game doesn\'t even come close to looking like that. Not even on my very high-end rig. The game runs at a decent 55 to 75 FPS and then dips down into the teens after laying waste to a room full of stupid AI enemies. As I\'ve progressed further into the game, the glitches and immersion breaking issues become more prevelant. It\'s not uncommon to see people driving around in invisible cars. My own car has blown up for no apparant reason a few times. The audio cuts out at random. Most of the original soundtrack is pretty lame and forgettable.\r\n\r\nThe gameplay is nothing special, unique, or mindblowingly awesome. It\'s generic and feels like a few games we\'ve all played in the past. If I didn\'t know better, I\'d have thought this was a cyberpunk mod for Fallout: New Vegas. None of the characters are memorable. V is an edgelord whose origins make zero difference since you will always end up in the same starting location after the prologue. Dialogue options won\'t adversely affect the outcome. It\'s nowhere near engaging as the options in KOTOR, Mass Effect 1 and 2, or the entire Witcher series. There\'s no real reason to become emotionally attached to any particular person. All of the vehicles handle like a forklift on ice. KB+mouse or Xbone pad have issues. Buttons sometimes don\'t respond. I crouch when I want to dodge, double tapping to dodge is beyond stupid, crouch works only half the time, some keybindings cannot be changed.\r\n\r\nThere are way better older games. Play those ones.', 2, 'April 14, 2021', 'English', 0, 0, 0, 'Slipstream', 2093619782),
(89, ' Wasted potential and overhyped product ', 'When this game was announced, GTA V hadn\'t been released yet. They made ambitious goals and gave us all hope for the future. Shortly after, GTA V released and changed the definition of what an open world could be. Since then several games have come out and the boundaries have been pushed further. RDR2 is the gold standard as of today.\r\n\r\nIt is unfortunate that Cyberpunk 2077 is of worse quality and has fewer capabilities than GTA V from 2013. Nothing new or groundbreaking is in this game. Watch Dogs gave us hacking and RDR2 is currently leading the way in physics, wanted systems, NPC interactions and so much more.\r\n\r\nIt really seems as though this was a failed project which had a good concept that marketing didn\'t want to let die. At the end of the day, this game was marketed as an open world RPG set in a dystopian world. What was delivered was a low quality, buggy game which has just enough features to be somewhat considered open world and didn\'t even have enough role playing to keep the RPG designation. I haven\'t been this disappointed since I read \'World War Z\' by Max Brooks and then watched the movie with Brad Pitt.\r\n\r\nMy only hope is that over the next few years is that CDPR makes this right and keeps rolling out updates.', 2, 'April 14, 2021', 'English', 0, 0, 0, 'Slipstream5000', 2093619782),
(90, ' Thoughts after full 100h+ playthrough ', 'NOTE: This review is from the perspective of someone looking for a good role-playing experience, keep this in mind while reading.\r\n\r\ntl:dr the game fails to deliver as an RPG\r\n\r\n1: The main quest is on rails with very little interactivity, i hope you like cutscenes, grab some popcorn.\r\n\r\n2: The world is huge but empty.\r\nThere is no meaningful difference between areas. The only real difference is visual, and how tough the enemies are. Even Skyrim has distinct cities that have unique questlines with the different guilds. There\'s tons of radiant quests, and very few hand crafted side quests. And even these are often the bottom of the barrel. (The monk quest is just kill enemies, get berated by an ungrateful guy then you\'re done). Barring the main quest, play the game for 4 hours doing side missions and you\'ve seen all the game has to offer.\r\n\r\n3: No (narrative) character customization. The life paths are a perfect microcosm of the lack of player autonomy. Everyone is a street kid. Your background means absolute squat in terms of the story, barring a few dialogue options which are just flavor text themselves. This theme applies to the rest of the game. There isn\'t \'your V.\' There is \'the V\' and you better like the box CDPR carved out for you.\r\n\r\n4: It has a looter shooter system, but is just worse than Borderlands in the execution. You will *never* have to grind to get passed a section, just equip the stuff with the highest numbers and you\'ll always do just fine so long as you don\'t go into zones labeled very high risk. I grew up on the original Diablo so I love loot driven \'RPGs\' and this fails at it spectacularly. There simply is no incentive for the loot.\r\n\r\nTo cap it off I\'ll just compare it to The Outer Worlds. The Outer Worlds is an extremely flawed game that I could spend hours criticizing and yet the game consistently delivers as an RPG in key areas where Cyberpunk fails.\r\n\r\nPlayer Autonomy\r\nInteresting NPCs\r\nWorld Interactivity\r\nRPG stat mechanics (stats, skills, etc)\r\nDialogue ', 2, 'April 14, 2021', 'English', 0, 0, 0, 'Spiritfarer', 2093619782),
(91, ' The 2013 teaser is more entertaining. ', 'How did this happen.\r\nPut aside the bugs.\r\nPut aside the performance problems.\r\nThe gameplay is so poor, upgrades are useless and not interesting to obtain...\r\nDriving is hell, musics are suprisingly forgetable.\r\nI waited for this game for so long, I was promised an RPG and I got this...', 2, 'April 14, 2021', 'English', 0, 0, 0, 'StarRenegades', 2093619782),
(92, ' Sadly, An Average Game ', 'Currently, the game is bad. CDPR outright lied in their marketing campaign, multiple times on multiple things. The \'out when it\'s ready\' is the biggest one. It is not ready. It plays like a buggy clone of Deus Ex: Human Revolution. Bugs, bugs, bugs, bugs everywhere.\r\n\r\nOptimisation and performance is terrible. Controls are clunky, the physics are all over the place. There might be a good story there, characters seem interesting. But I can\'t tell since all I see is floating items and I\'m constantly being shot into space when driving my car.\r\n\r\nI do not recommend, wait for a discount, maybe they\'ll fix some of it by then.', 1, 'April 14, 2021', 'English', 0, 0, 0, 'StarringAdamWest', 2093619782),
(93, ' Legit kind of terrible. ', '1) The performance issues are killing my experience. Tried changing the settings for hours but the impact on framerate is very inconsistent.\r\n2) V\'s movement feels very bad. It\'s hard to explain, but it feels clumsy.\r\n3) The game gave me dizziness at first, but increasing the FOV helped.\r\n4) The UI screens are so ugly. ', 2, 'April 14, 2021', 'English', 0, 0, 0, 'StateofPlay', 2093619782),
(94, ' Game synopsis in the gog store... ', 'Farcry 3 meets borderlands meets the witcher 3 on launch. Insipid sidequests, horrible gameplay, performances decreasing rapidly over time until you have to restart your entire system.\r\nThis is a review, not a critique.\r\nWait a few more months before considering buying it, especially if your system isn\'t upper high end.', 2, 'April 14, 2021', 'English', 0, 0, 0, 'StreamDream', 2093619782),
(95, ' Consistently Unstable ', 'It it\'s current state the game is unplayable. Performance in 2.5K is painfully low on RTX 2080 with RTX on, controls feel clunky and i can\'t find a way to turn off mouse smoothing (feels like it\'s always on).\r\nWill definitely try it again next year, after a few more months of polishing and bugfixing, but for now - pass.', 2, 'April 14, 2021', 'English', 0, 0, 0, 'TerraBlight', 2093619782),
(96, ' Mixed Feelings ', 'The world itself is jaw dropping.  Unfortunately just about every other system in the game outside of art, writing &amp; music/audio are unacceptably shallow in a deep \'RPG\' from CD Projekt Red.\r\n\r\nNPC\'s seem to have only 2 states -- walking around aimlessly, and when you bump into someone, everyone in a 5 mile radius hits the deck or runs for their lives.  That\'s about it.  The wanted system in this game is also atrocious.  GTA 3 had a more complex police interaction system than this, sadly.\r\n\r\nCombat &amp; weapons are a ton of fun.  Each weapon is meticulously modeled and animated, and they all feel &amp; sound great to use.  However, stealth and hacking are a total waste of time.  None of the abilities or interactions with the world are interesting, and all it does is pad out an enemy encounter by making it take 10x as long to clear.  Unfortunately, if you had dreams of becoming a netrunner like I did, there\'s very little here to entice you longer than 20 minutes.\r\n\r\nSide quests and gigs are unfathomably boring.  I remember side quests in The Witcher as some of the best writing &amp; quest design in the industry.  Unfortunately, side quests here feel like they borrowed from the MMO formula.  Instead of a handful of meaningful side quest that take unexpected turns or tell engaging stories, we\'re given 300 points of interest that involve a bunch of enemies to kill and a few crates to loot.  And how do you meet these notorious fixers?  Let\'s just have them call you every 5 minutes as a floating head on your screen.\r\n\r\nThankfully I haven\'t experienced a single performance issue, but I know the majority of people have been.  Running everything on Ultra without RTX at 1080p.\r\n\r\nAgain -- the game itself is absolutely stunning.  No other open world holds a candle to Night City.  But much like the corporations in Night City, it is simply a facade that tries to hide the fact that it is a shallow husk the deeper you look.\r\n\r\nHurts to say it, but CDPR bit off WAY more than they could chew here. ', 4, 'April 14, 2021', 'English', 0, 0, 0, 'Terraria', 2093619782),
(97, ' Depressingly Underwhelming ', 'Current Cyberpunk 2077 impressions. 7 hours 47 minutes.\r\n        Jank:\r\n            - Too janky for AAA. Virtually every aspect of the game is at least *somewhat* bugged.\r\n            - Poorly optimized no matter the hardware\r\n            - Audio mixing seems off. The dialogue is often not loud enough for the music.\r\n\r\n        Narrativ:\r\n            - V has more personality than he/she should.\r\n            - Female V\'s voice acting is goofy. She\'s trying to sound \'badass\' but instead sounds like a young boy pretending to be older.\r\n            - Several contrived story beats.\r\n            - I\'ve no interest in Keanu or Silverhand, but it\'s at least 50% his story, not yours - the player.\r\n\r\n        Gameplay:\r\n            - The skilltree is boring. Many %-bonuses.\r\n            - Can\'t hide the come fuck me arrows (objective markers).\r\n            - No universal character death. Can\'t kill those obnoxious YouTube \'badass.\'\r\n            - Can\'t reject cyberwear. No purist runs allowed.\r\n            - Melee stealth build is comepletely pointless thanks to instakill options.\r\n            - Stealth in general is extremely simple.\r\n            - AI is braindead in many combat scenarios.\r\n            - In general, the game is very easy even on the hardest difficulty.\r\n            - Loot is entirely pointless.\r\n\r\n        Other:\r\n            - Nudity censorship in-game no matter the settings or what was promised (Underwear bug/censor).\r\n\r\n        Current score: 7.0 (Subject to later change)', 2, 'April 14, 2021', 'English', 0, 0, 0, 'TheBasement', 2093619782),
(98, ' Patch 1.1 Broken the game. ', 'Pre-ordered, installed on 7 December. Playing (ha) on a Ryzen 5, Samsung SSD T7 and AMD RX 5700 *drivers updated today\r\n\r\nBelieve me, I regret having to post this review as I am a big CDPR homer and longtime GoG user\r\n\r\nBUT\r\n\r\nat its current state, the game is unplayable. Had 15 crashes to desktop in barely 20 minutes of play, audio glitching, NPCs not moving.\r\n\r\nHappy to change my review once I can get to at least 30 (10 would be a good start) minutes of uninterrupted playtime.\r\n\r\nRight now, a complete mess. ', 2, 'April 14, 2021', 'English', 0, 0, 0, 'TheCountLucanor', 2093619782);
INSERT INTO `gogcom_comments_baldursgate3` (`commentId`, `comment_title`, `comment_text`, `game_rating`, `comment_date`, `comment_language`, `helpful_comment_for_all`, `Un_helpful_comment_for_all`, `helpful_comment_for_this_user`, `comment_username`, `comment_gameid`) VALUES
(99, ' Wait ~2 more years ', 'Lets start with the good\r\n- Night city is absolutely beatiful, the art team did a fantastic job, however it feels all feels fake as you cannot explore interiors outside of story missions and shops.\r\n- The soundtrack is great\r\n- Story is good and there are some pretty great side quests.\r\n\r\nThe Bad\r\n- This game is advertised as an RPG, but you are given few meaningful choices, the only ones that exist were shown in the marketing and the ending. It gives the impression that (bugs aside) this game is unfinished as even those choices are more flavour than anything. There were many times I wanted to do\r\n- The bugs, while I got fairly lucky and only really experienced UI bugs the state of this game for others is utterly unacceptable.\r\n- Performance, with a 1080 ti and 2600x I get about 45 fps in interiors and 25-35 outside, lowering settings only decreases gpu usage and does not improve framrate (I actually expericed lower lows after lowering settings)\r\n- UI is absolutely TERRIBLE and is clearly designed only with controllers in mind.\r\n- AI is terrible\r\n- Guns combat is average, but melee combat is poor and floaty\r\n- Driving is bad\r\n- You can\'t remap all your buttons (more proof this game is designed only with consoles in mind) also dodging is mapped to double tapping a direction, I don\'t know who though that was a good idea.\r\n- People calling you all the time to do boring repetative jobs.\r\n- I wish it would take itself more serouisly, I don\'t want a game where I can chase people with a vibrator.\r\n\r\nConclusion\r\nThis game is a buggy mess and seems like it is unfinished, beyond that it is surrounded by false advertising to make it sound like an RPG, when in fact you have no control over the story other than the ending. It should have been delayed another year or two in order to make a game worth $60. There is still a decent game here but I would not buy it in its current state and it is worth closer to $40. Honestly I\'m just sad, this could have been something amazing but its just not. ', 2, 'April 14, 2021', 'English', 0, 0, 0, 'TheFrame', 2093619782),
(100, ' Wait a bit... but don\'t hope for much ', 'As you can see, there are 786 games so far in my GOG account. As a ten-year unconditional supporter, I assume I am pretty qualified to say something negative about THIS game based on my 25 hour of play.\r\n\r\nBut I am not saying it today.\r\n\r\nI have only one question to ask: CDPR, please, look at me in the eye and say this is what you have promised 8 years ago and been working very hard on since. ', 2, 'April 14, 2021', 'English', 0, 0, 0, 'TheLonging', 2093619782),
(101, ' Not nearly what it could have been ', 'World is beautiful and it has huge potential, but it feels like it was squandered away. Here is my list:\r\n-It\'s not open world when you lock sections of it based on story.\r\n-Artefact glitches\r\n-Huge amount of useless guns, worse then Borderlands\r\n-Locked key bindings\r\n-Performance issues\r\n-Pedestrians pop in and out all the time\r\n-Cops start shooting at you for literally nothing, bot don\'t say a thing when I am walking down the street with a bazooka in hand\r\n-No reason to go to your apartment and use the stash as it is pretty much useless\r\n-So many things but nothing worth to interact with\r\n-Was hoping to go in a bar and do braindance and whatnot (even GTA 5 had lap dances and sex in cars)\r\n-Gun vendors sell the same stuff\r\n-Hacking is useless and a joke, in the tabletop you could surf the net\r\n-Stealth is a joke\r\n-Gun levelling... are you serious? What is there to level up on a bloody gun? Oiling the mechanism?\r\n-Not to mention clothing levelling. Changing the shoelaces? Sewing on new buttons?\r\n-Crafting is a joke, not even close to what Fallout 4 has\r\n-No hidden gems of places with collectibles and such\r\n-UI is crap, it\'s sensory overload and hard to navigate\r\n\r\nAs a person who loves Fallout 3, NV and 4, I feel like this game is a major step back in open world RPGs. I am deeply disappointed so far. No matter how good the story is, or how interesting the characters are the world doesn\'t invite you in. You don\'t feel the need having to go in to a small alleyway, or dark corner as there is nothing there. Nothing to see, nothing to experience.\r\n\r\nIt was developed for 7 years? If this would have been out in 2015, I would have said, that it is decent. But after all the previous advancements in open world rpgs, this is a massive let-down.\r\n\r\nHaven\'t finished Act1 yet. If the game won\'t open up more and give me more options in terms of crafting, hacking, stashing, buying new apartments, etc... then this review won\'t change. Might just play one of the old Fallout games or GTA 5 at this point.', 2, 'April 14, 2021', 'English', 0, 0, 0, 'ThemeHospital', 2093619782),
(102, ' Missing promised features', 'Oh dear. Oh dear oh dear oh dear.\r\n\r\nUpdated graphics drivers (and other drivers just to be thorough) prior to install.\r\n\r\nLowered my expectations on my humble set-up being able to run anything other than medium/lower end settings.\r\n\r\nDisabled Win10 DPI on the game exe.\r\n\r\nThis is pitiful. I simply cannot express my disappointment. Floating trees throughout; crashes during character creation, 14 fps at worst with a 1080 and massivley ramped down settings/scaling, T-posing spotted, graphics settings which seemingly make no difference...\r\n\r\n... Lord only knows what state the game must have been in back at the original April 2020 release postponement if THIS is the result of 8 months extra fixing.\r\n\r\n2 stars because we could always get the magic update in coming weeks.\r\n\r\nAssured my hype was severely tempered. I\'d be massively disappointed if this game had 10% the publicity and hype ot received, let alone the supposed game of the century.\r\n\r\nWait until the game is patched, at least once if not twice before getting this. ', 2, 'April 14, 2021', 'English', 0, 0, 0, 'TheOutergWorlds', 2093619782),
(103, ' Undelivered', 'Don\'t bother reading 5-star reviews that are showering the game with praise. Some are trying to convince themselves that the long wait and emotional investment was worth it.\r\n\r\nEven with the recommended specs and updated drivers, the game runs terribly, if one can even say it runs at all. It\'s got a ridiculous amount of bugs, frames tank every 2 or 3 minutes, and the game crashed more than once within the first 20 minutes. Turns out crunching your workers with 100-hour weeks only makes them perform poorly, who would have guessed?\r\n\r\nGameplay itself its very poor. It\'s a jack of all trades, but none of the play styles are actually as rich and developed as dedicated FPS or stealth games or as CDPR might have thought, they\'re average at best. Also, key bindings are awful and feel like a console port.\r\n\r\nI can\'t speak about the story itself because I haven\'t finished it, but from what I have played the only thing cyberpunk about the game is the aesthetic. I don\'t wish to fan any flames so I won\'t mention the most likely reason CDPR decided to completely cut off the inherently political nature of the genre, but in doing so CP2077 just became \'wow cool guns and neon lights\'.\r\n\r\nIf the only thing keeping you from buying this game is the bugs, then just wait 3 or 4 months until they\'re all squashed. Otherwise I\'m gonna have to say: hard pass.', 2, 'April 14, 2021', 'English', 0, 0, 0, 'theOuterWorld', 2093619782),
(104, ' I tried. ', 'I had the utmost faith in CDPR with this game. I have been a huge cyberpunk fan and this was to the ultimate experience...The gameplay videos sold me on this instantly and was hyped for many years.\r\n\r\nUnfortunately, this didn\'t have a happy ending. Many, many people already have said a lot about performance and bugs so I won\'t bore you with those details. My gripe comes with the completely dead city. The videos had initially touted the most advanced open-world experience to date. I\'m sorry, but this doesn\'t even compare to the earlier of Grand Theft Autos.\r\n\r\nTo start, the NPCs have no real AI. Probably a simple routine that checks for violence and they cower in fear. No real response to stimuli just the same generic voice line when you interact. Half the time, they are just in the way and the police AI is even worst, they just spawn randomly on you and forget you were every alive after you move slightly away. For a game that claimed to have the most believable city \'to date\' with their \'greatly enhanced crowd and community system\' it was sorely lacking.\r\n\r\nThe city itself honestly feels like a backdrop to the main story line, nothing more. It doesn\'t stand on its own. It just feels like one large billboard that looks good from far away.\r\n\r\nCombat including gunplay and brawling are very clunky and just tedious in the harder difficulties. Increasing HP and damage is not a good way to increase difficulty. I\'m tired of devs using that to be lazy. Instead of making AI smarter, they make them into bullet sponges.\r\n\r\nThe only saving grace for this game is the amazing main story, voice cast, and level design for main missions. It is well done and it makes me believe that the team originally had planned this level of finesse for the entire city but ran out of time or were forced to strip most of it out. Overall, it\'s enjoyable if you take it for what it is: A generic FPS with a good story. This is NOT an Open-world RPG. Stick to Witcher if you want to have that kind of experience', 2, 'April 14, 2021', 'English', 0, 0, 0, 'TheSuffering', 2093619782),
(105, ' Not finished yet... ', 'You will have a very hard time playing (enjoying?) this game.\r\n\r\n1. Most of the essential keys can not be re-bound (\'binding FAILED\') - and some keys are hard-locked for absolutely no reason (like the interaction key is and will always be \'f\', period). CDPR have not learned from the mistakes made in Witcher 3 - a game I couldn\'t play for years because of these restrictions.\r\nThis alone results in a one star review because it completely breaks the game for me.\r\n\r\n2. CP2077 is not ready for prime time as it suffers from abysmal performance. If you don\'t have a very high-end setup you might be in for a slide show unless you reduce the level of detail considerably. The official system requirements for CP2077 are clearly misleading.\r\n\r\n3. Updating to the latest drivers solved most of the graphical glitches I had on my 1080 Ti. BTW this 1080 Ti was able to push about 40 fps at 1440p and custom medium-low settings.\r\n\r\nI\'m waiting for the devs to fix 1. but won\'t hesitate to ask for a refund if they refuse to do so.', 2, 'April 14, 2021', 'English', 0, 0, 0, 'TheVoid', 2093619782),
(107, ' Deception at its finest ', 'I\'m sad to say that the game in its current state is unplayable for me. I have a GTX 1060 6GB and a\r\ni7-9700k. It is impossible to achieve a stable frame rate even on lower settings. I have no doubt that\r\nCD Project will fix most of the problems eventually but they need a lot more time. Cyberpunk 2077 should\'ve been released in 2021 but I suppose they needed all that X-mas money. 1 year from now\r\nThis game will probably get a 5/5 from me. But I recommend you avoid it unless you have a extremely powerful computer.', 2, 'April 14, 2021', 'English', 0, 0, 0, 'Torchlight', 2093619782),
(108, ' No expectations and I was still let down ', 'Positives:\r\n+ fantastic writing\r\n+ excellent atmosphere\r\n+ great quests where choices matter\r\n\r\nAverage:\r\n~ character customization and development. On the surface there is a plethora of options but in reality they do not influence gameplay too much.  Ie. perks: +5% reload speed here, + 10% explosive damage there etc. +5% resistance here etc. Same goes for weapon choices\r\n~ combat is just ok, nothing to complain or write home about\r\n\r\n\r\nNegatives:\r\n- poor optimization. Changing video setting from medium to low for me had no visible impact on performance.\r\n- console port quality level of UI and controls. Game feels very much designed for consoles and controllers\r\n-bugs ie. graphical glitches or quests not updating and not progressing.\r\n\r\nOverall solid but definitely not mind blowing experience.', 2, 'April 14, 2021', 'English', 0, 0, 0, 'TrekNation', 2093619782),
(109, ' Empty, boring, buggy trash ', 'Even with the performance issues and bugs, I can\'t give this game more than a 6/10. The game feels bland to play. It\'s RPG mechanics are lackluster. The writing is not as engaging as Witcher 3\'s. I didn\'t have super high expectations for this game but even I am disappointed by this. Night City looks pretty and that\'s the highest amount of praise I can give the game honestly. It\'s not a bad game by any means, it\'s just boring and uninteresting much of the time, which is probably one of the game\'s biggest sins. I expect more from this game, considering all its development time and its delays. You should too. ', 2, 'April 14, 2021', 'English', 0, 0, 0, 'Unbound:WorldsApart', 2093619782),
(110, ' inexcusable ', 'Multiple key settings such as F, O, P are fixed and cannot be changed. It is very disappointing that you can\'t even change the interact key.\r\nIt doesn\'t hold up to the requirements of a PC game', 2, 'April 14, 2021', 'English', 0, 0, 0, 'UserAcc', 2093619782),
(111, ' CDPR lost my respect ', 'I am flabbergasted by Cyberpunk 2077. I was expecting an awesome open world I could role-play in (you know, because it\'s a role playing game) and instead I found myself faced with limited customization, a lack of meaningful dialogue, and a character named \'v\' that I\'m positive is just like everyone else\'s character named \'v\' I played all three \'origin stories\' and they had no impact on anything. V is as bland as oatmeal made with water. It\'s almost like I\'m playing Fallout 4 again except the menus are worse and the combat is weird. The one positive difference from Fallout 4 is that V will say what you pressed. I am always waiting for the next game to let me create my own character. It\'s my favorite part of gaming. I thought I would be able to pretend to be a character I wanted to be, but instead my choices made no difference.\r\n\r\nWhat\'s going on with having to pick up all the random junk lying around? It\'s hard to even line V up to pick up all the useless garbage that goes into the poorly designed inventory. There\'s no feedback in combat. Did that guy take damage? Did I take damage? Better look at the HP bar that blends in with the whole screen--yep I\'m almost dead. Never would have known I even took damage otherwise. The controls feel uncomfortable and combat is just not fun for me.  The glitches can be funny, but are mostly just annoying. V became naked in the apartment mirror and in the ripperdoc\'s chair, and V has the weirdest sleep animations I have ever seen. NPCs pop out of thin air, characters walk through closed elevators, no one has anything important to say, and I haven\'t seen anywhere I could explore for fun. It\'s a lifeless environment. It\'s like they spent all the money on creating a sweet vibe and forgot they had to make a game to play too.\r\n\r\nAnyway, this game needs like ten updates, and it\'s annoying that they advertised this game as a finished groundbreaking masterpiece when it is clearly just an average game with an interesting setting.', 2, 'April 14, 2021', 'English', 0, 0, 0, 'Vangers', 2093619782),
(112, ' shallow, lifeless game - with some hope. ', 'For the first hours of heavily scripted prologue the game looks and feels great. But then the veil drops, youre introduced to the open world of Night City and it is just... so underwhelming. It gradually starts occurring to you that this game is a poor mans version of GTA V, with a cliche story and annoying mechanics:\r\n\r\n- NPCs are really really dumb - they dont interact with the world, dont really react to your actions apart from crouching when scared. They walk without any purpose like mindless zombies spitting out one liners when you try to talk to them. Nothing like in Skyrim, where NPCs had their daily routines and full dialogue trees, not even like in GTA V or RDR 2, where they seemed dumb but more conscious of their environment.\r\n\r\n- Cars - driving is just OKAY, feels a bit like Sleeping Dogs, BUT - in story moments when youre the passenger the ride feels sooo stiff and artificial its almost funny. And completely immersion breaking.\r\n\r\n- Road traffic is as dumb as pedestrian NPCs - you can jam whole blocks of streets by parking your bike bit off the pavement.\r\n\r\n- When you do crime, the police just likes to spawn from nowhere even in dead-end alleys.\r\n\r\n- No car tuning/modification.\r\n\r\n- No garages to store your stolen cars in.\r\n\r\n- No hairstylists, tattoo artists, plastic surgeons - what you make your character look at the start they stay that way till the end.\r\n\r\n- Clothes are not about style but their armour rating, so you eventually end up looking like a dumpster.\r\n\r\n- Not much to do in general in the Night City apart from missions. No side activities, mini games, interactions. Despite great visuals, the city feels dead and fake.\r\n\r\n- Bullet sponge enemies - something that breaks all immersion for me - forget about killing the baddies in one headshot with your powerful new smart rifle - its gonna be more like 5-10 headshots.\r\n\r\n- Bugs everywhere!\r\n\r\nThe games nothing like they promised, feels shallow and rushed, and Im afraid no amount of patches will fix that. ', 2, 'April 14, 2021', 'English', 0, 0, 0, 'WackyWheels', 2093619782),
(113, ' Cut content everywhere ', 't\'s with a heavy heart and after a lot of \'fixing\' done that I\'m writing this...\r\n\r\nTo summarise the things I\'ve tried:\r\n clean install of the latest GFX drivers,\r\n checked the integrity multiple time,\r\n re-downloaded the entire game and\r\n even dropped all settings to low.\r\nThe result is the same: crash to desktop.\r\n\r\nThe furthest I\'ve managed to get is going through the character creation (x6 now) and ripping off the patch off V\'s jacket in the nomad path.\r\n\r\nTo CDPR - I really rooted for you guys. I absolutly support DRM free games and addored playing the Witcher I/II/III but this is pretty bad. Here\'s my peace of mind if it even matters at this point: In the future please don\'t announce a launch date until you know you have a well polished game on your hands.\r\n\r\nAlso, word to the wise: tired, overworked, developers doing \'voluntary\' (or otherwise) crunch end up creating more bugs than they fix (look it up, there\'s research on this particular topic). This basically tends to create an environment ripe for unplayable and unstable software messes rolling on marketing hype.\r\n\r\nI know hotfixes and large patches will eventually be published and then the majority that had issues will be able to enjoy a mostly stable version of the game. To be clear this is not a good attitude which is sadly all too prevalent in the software industry. I get it, software is hard and take a lot of time and care to get right but this \'let\'s ship it now and deal with getting it to work lated\' kinda attitude is just plain bad in my opinion. Ship it when it is actually done.\r\n\r\nI\'ll edit this if and when I can actually play a game without crashing.', 2, 'April 14, 2021', 'English', 0, 0, 0, 'Wasteland3', 2093619782),
(114, ' BUGS and FRUSTRATION ', 'Quite frankly, it plays horrible with keyboard and mouse. There\'s mouse acceleration with no way of turning it off exacerbated by the fairly above average input-lag this game has and actions are mapped out with gamepad controllers in mind making it unintuitive and cumbersome using a keyboard, driving is also entirely made with analog input in mind making steering with a keyboard feel ultra touchy to the point of feeling near broken and certainly not any fun. Remapping keys also seems to be limited and/or broken, can\'t toggle crouch or aim.\r\n\r\nThere\'s quite the list of options to toggle in settings though, but lacks any AA options and you\'re stuck with TAA with no way to turn it off, creating fever-haze like oddly blurry visuals with the frame pacing/input feel issues that are common tradeoffs with TAA, ultimately baring you from setting the option that will have the most impact on the visuals.\r\n\r\nI\'ve only played 2 hours of the game, but it\'s been an unpleasant struggle with the issues above to the point I will now attempt something I\'ve never done with over 140 GOG games to my credit, request a refund.  This game turned out to be a disappointment I did not see coming', 1, 'April 14, 2021', 'English', 0, 0, 0, 'WeCauseScenes', 2093619782),
(115, ' Moral of the story; don\'t preorder ', 'The gameplay is decent, but almost everything else is either extremely buggy or runs rather poorly. I wasn\'t expecting max settings on my dated GPU (R9 Fury) but I was expecting something more than 1080p30 on low settings considering it\'s supposedly the recommended GPU. The plethora of glitches and dumb AI also don\'t help.\r\nIt\'s a shame because it seems like the game itself has a lot of effort put into it, but they didn\'t bother putting any effort into any of the technical aspects, to the point where the game feels less like a CDPR game and more like a typical rushed Bethesda game, only it arguably runs even worse.', 2, 'April 14, 2021', 'English', 0, 0, 0, 'Whateverland', 2093619782),
(116, ' An early-access game sold for $60 ', 'Cyberpunk 2077 reaches for the stars and for the most part delivers on its promises. As incredible as the game is,  I recommend that people give CD Projekt Red a few more weeks to iron out some of the more glaring bugs before jumping in. Cyberpunk 2077 is a dream and will only get better with time. ', 3, 'April 14, 2021', 'English', 0, 0, 0, 'Zombotron', 2093619782),
(119, ' BUGS and Tab', 'Quite frankly, it plays horrible with keyboard and mouse. There\'s mouse acceleration with no way of turning it off exacerbated by the fairly above average input-lag this game has and actions are mapped out with gamepad controllers in mind making it unintuitive and cumbersome using a keyboard, driving is also entirely made with analog input in mind making steering with a keyboard feel ultra touchy to the point of feeling near broken and certainly not any fun. Remapping keys also seems to be limited and/or broken, can\'t toggle crouch or aim.', 2, 'April 16, 2020', 'English', 0, 0, 0, '1000NewOne', 2093619782),
(123, 'testing comments by admin', '* test rating ang overall rating and verified overall rating\n*test all filter you clicked to show less comment\n', 1, 'April 20, 2021', 'English', 0, 0, 0, 'AustinHigh', 2093619782),
